title: beat 'n eat frosting
directions: Mix egg white, sugar, cream of tartar and vanilla in a small deep bowl.
Add boiling water.
Beat with electric mixer until stiff peaks form.

title: instant cocoa
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
To serve, use 1 to 2 teaspoons cocoa with 1 cup hot water.

title: beef tips and noodles
directions: Brown beef tips in vegetable oil until cooked through.
Add onion soup mix, mushroom soup, fresh mushrooms and wine.
Simmer on low heat for several hours.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: spinach sprout salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Add salad greens, spinach and bean sprouts.

title: "easy" lasagna
directions: Cook meat and onion until meat is browned.
Drain off fat. Stir in spaghetti sauce and set aside.
Do not cook lasagna noodles!
Beat eggs and Ricotta or cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper together; set aside.

title: sausage patties(less fat, no chemicals)
directions: In food processor, mince the parsley and onion by turning the machine on and off.
Reserve them.
Mix the pork and fat in a bowl and divide the mixture into three batches.
Put 1 batch in the work bowl and chop by turning the machine on and off until it reaches the desired texture.
Transfer to a large bowl; repeat with remaining two batches.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix gelatin, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together in top of double boiler.
Stir in milk and water.
Beat in egg yolks, then add the pumpkin.
Place over boiling water.
Cook until mixture is heated through.
Remove from heat.
Chill until mixture begins to set.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Add 1/4 cup sugar; beat until very stiff.
Fold pumpkin mixture into egg whites.
Turn into pie shell and when ready to serve, top with whipped cream.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: big mama's buttermilk cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs together until creamy.
Add flour and soda, which has been dissolved in 2 tablespoons of water, with buttermilk and flavoring; beat well.
Pour in well greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hamburger chow mein
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger.
Drain hamburger.
Mix all ingredients.
Add cooked hamburger.
Bake 1/2 hour covered with foil; bake 1/2 hour uncovered.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles if desired.

title: pizza dough
directions: Put yeast in bowl, then add warm water.
Mix until dissolved. Add rest of ingredients.
Mix good with spoon and let rise 5 minutes.
Beat down and may need a little flour to spread out on pizza pan.
The best pizza sauce is Contadina.
Spread over crust. Add pepperoni, mushrooms, sausage, onion, ham or whatever you enjoy, then add Mozzarella cheese on top and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: nuts and bolts party mix
directions: Microwave Method:
Heat butter in 12 x 8-inch dish at Medium-high 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, garlic and salt.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Cook at High 6 to 7 minutes or until butter is absorbed and mixture is crispy.
Stir occasionally.
Let cool before serving or storing.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: gingerbread
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a large bowl and beat well. Dissolve soda in hot water and add to beaten mixture.
Sift in flour.
Beat well.
Add boiling water and beat lightly and quickly.
Pour in pans and bake 45 minutes in a moderate oven (350°).
Cut in squares and top with a generous mound of unsweetened whipped cream.

title: ice cream
directions: Pour 2 cans of milk into pot.
Mix 2 cups sugar and 2 tablespoons flour and pour into pot; stir together.
Add other 2 cans of milk.
Put 4 egg yolks (beaten) and 3 cans water.
Add flavor.
Heat.
Beat egg whites; add to pot.
Heat until bubbles appear.
Stir constantly.
Cook on medium heat.
If any lumps, strain.
Pour all into freezer and cut bananas in slices.
May add other fruit of choice and whipped cream.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery in shortening.
Stir in rice, add both cans of soup and water, pour into casserole and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 30 more minutes. Add chow mein noodles on top and bake uncovered 15 minutes longer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix butter and cornflakes.
Cook rice.
Mix cooked rice with all other ingredients.
Pour in medium size casserole dish and spread cornflakes on top.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Freezes well.

title: raspberry lemon tea
directions: Steep tea bags in hot water just as if you were to make regular tea. Dissolve tub of raspberry mix into the tea. Add enough water to make one quart of this mixture. Add the ginger ale to this mixture just before serving. Waiting to add the ginger ale at the time of serving keeps the mixture sparkling. Using sugar-free ginger ale and caffeine free tea makes a drink that tastes the same.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix ingredients.
Grease and flour large cookie sheet.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
After cooled, glaze, frost or top with Cool Whip.

title: venison heart
directions: Cut heart in half and trim off inedible parts.
Marinate in a mixture of wine, vinegar, salt, peppercorns, mustard, onion, bay leaves and garlic powder.
Roll hearts in flour and fry in margarine in a skillet until well done.

title: old-fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat
oven to 425°.
Mix
pumpkin,
eggs
and
salt. Spices can be mixed with
sugar.
Mix
all filling ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes and then reduce heat to 350°. Continue baking for
minutes.
Do not underbake. Cool completely.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: dump cake
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan in order given. Sprinkle nuts on top and slice butter over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let cool.

title: corn bread with hot peppers
directions: Mix and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 450° until brown on top.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Combine beef and sauce.
Heat for 5 minutes.
Mix cooked spaghetti, butter, eggs and Parmesan cheese together.
Place 1/2 of this in an ungreased pie pan.
Layer with sauce, Ricotta and spaghetti mixture.
Add remaining spaghetti and sauce again.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with Mozzarella and bake for 10 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: one bowl chocolate cake
directions: Sift the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl and add to the rest of ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
This is a very moist cake; easy to make and no eggs needed.

title: hawaiian coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks, one at a time and beat well. Add butter, milk and soda.
Mix well. Add flour.
Mix well. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix well into your flour.
Mix mixture with a spoon, then pecans and coconut.
Heat oven to 350°. Bake 25 minutes. Makes four 8-inch layer cakes.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, add spices to taste.
Drain grease. Add spaghetti sauce and simmer.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water in covered saucepan over low heat for 2 minutes. Add broccoli and cauliflower.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes longer.
Drain. Combine all vegetables. Combine oil, vinegar and seasonings.
Pour over vegetables. Cover and chill at least 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: hooch cookies
directions: Cream oleo, shortening and sugars.
Add 2 eggs.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture the flour mixture.
Blend well and add vanilla, oatmeal and chocolate chips. Add the nuts, M&M's and peanut butter chips.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: overnight coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots and onions in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over coleslaw mixture; toss lightly to coat. Cover and refrigerate overnight, tossing occasionally.
Yield:
8 servings (about 41 calories per serving).

title: mexican caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Drain again. Serve with chips or fresh veggies.

title: chili fudge
directions: Spread half of the cheese into a greased rectangular open pan. Beat eggs and combine with the picante.
Spread the mixture on the bottom layer of cheese and top with remaining cheese.
Bake the "fudge" 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Chill and cut into small squares.
(Guaranteed to clog your arteries!)

title: salsa
directions: Bring to boil, then simmer 5-10 minutes.
Pack in hot jars.

title: steaks on the grill
directions: Mix the ingredients. Blend in blender for best results.
Place steaks in glass dish; cover steaks with the sauce.
Marinate for 4 to 6 hours and steaks are ready to grill!

title: quick turkey chili
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms, jalapenos and turkey burger until burger is browned.
Add beans, corn, olives and tomato sauce. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with dollop of sour cream and shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place chunks in dish and cover with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This makes a pretty dish.

title: thanksgiving applesauce cake
directions: Grease and flour (can use 1 long or 2 round cake pans). Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with applesauce.
Add nuts, raisins and cut-up orange gum candy.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In crock-pot, add beef, salt, garlic and pepper.
Cook on high until beef is done.
Add all other ingredients; cook on high 1 hour or may simmer all day.

title: spinach balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill several hours (2 to 3).
Shape into walnut size balls. Bake for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Spinach balls may be frozen before baking.

title: low-fat chocolate pudding milk shake
directions: Pour milk into blender container.
Add remaining ingredients and cover.
Blend at highest speed 15 seconds or until smooth. Serve at once.
(Mixture will thicken as it stands.
Thin with additional milk if necessary.)

title: bohemian slaw
directions: In a large casserole dish, alternate layers of vegetables. Season every potato layer.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Cover tightly. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
May be topped with Cheez Whiz before serving.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Start at 10:00 p.m. the night before.
Grease Bundt pan. Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan.
Arrange rolls around.
Pour dry pudding mix over rolls.
Mix butter, sugar and cinnamon together. Pour over rolls.
Cover pan with towel.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Mmmmm, good!

title: sour cherry jello
directions: Bring cherries, sugar and water to boil.
Pour over Jell-O and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and let set.

title: irish creme liqueur
directions: Start with God the Father and 1 Lord Jesus Christ (2 Cor. 8:6).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Debone it.
Put into large bowl and add all other ingredients. Mix all together and pour into greased Pyrex dish and add remaining dressing mix on top.
Dot it with 1/2 stick margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Bake in a tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Dust with confectioners sugar or:

title: the compromise cake
directions: Grease bottom of a 10-inch tube pan; line bottom of pan with wax paper.
Grease and flour lining and pan; set aside.
Combine applesauce and soda; set aside.
Combine raisins, dates and pecans; set aside.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Melt margarine and salt.
Put pecans in pan and pour margarine over it.
Then sprinkle brown sugar and stir in.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 300° to 325° for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: passover broccoli casserole *
directions: Steam frozen broccoli in microwave.
Place broccoli in 9 x 9-inch pan.
In bowl, mix melted butter, cottage cheese, potato starch, eggs, grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour over broccoli. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until edges turn brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: cream of chicken with shrimp
directions: Use baking pan.
Line bottom with dry beef.
Put chicken breast on top.
Cook bacon strips separately; now put on top of breast.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: olive craver's chicken dressing
directions: Pour chicken broth over broken bread and cracker crumbs.
Soak and cool.
Add eggs, celery, parsley and dry ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown on top and bottom.

title: tropical torte cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking powder together and cut in margarine with a fork or pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Beat egg slightly with milk and stir into flour mixture, mixing well. Spread evenly over the bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Spoon well drained pineapple in an even layer over crust.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in casserole dish.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: You get some cupcake mix.
Then you make the cupcakes.
Put sprinkles in and eggs in.
Stir with the mixer.
Put them in a pan and bake them for 14 minutes on warm.
Then you take them out of the oven and put them on a towel to cool.
When they are cooled, put any color of icing on them.
If you have a little girl, she can lick the spatula and the beaters so they will look all shiny and clean.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Work cheeses together, then add remaining ingredients.
Roll into a ball and roll in crushed nuts.
Chopped olives may be added if desired.
Serve on a bed of parsley or watercress.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add margarine.
Beat until fluffy. Add yolks one at a time; add vanilla and buttermilk alternately with soda and flour which have been sifted together.
Add coconut and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) layer pans, greased.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: mama's nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs that have been beaten to a froth. Sift flour with baking powder and add alternately with milk. Next add chopped nuts and flavoring. Bake in layer pans in a moderate oven until done.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef in large ovenproof pan (6-quart).
Salt and pepper meat to taste and add onion, bouillon cubes, cream of mushroom soup, water and sauerkraut.
Stir thoroughly; add noodles. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally and add more water if necessary.
If too watery toward end of baking, remove cover.

title: john's play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients well and cook over low heat until dough pulls away from pan.
Knead with hands until playdough is smooth in texture.
Store in tightly closed containers in a cool, dark place.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter, sugars and vanilla. Beat in egg.
Add cocoa and milk. Combine flour and baking powder. Fold into creamed mixture with walnuts and chocolate chips.
Roll teaspoonfuls of dough into balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes before removing to wire racks to cool.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: swedish pie
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla, salt and egg.
Add flour and baking powder.
Fold in walnuts and apples.
Pour into greased pie pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake
cake
mix
in
rectangular pan according to directions. Prepare
Jell-O
(any
flavor desired to blend with pie filling selected)
according to directions with 2 cups boiling water. Place
mixture
in
sink
filled
with cold water for 5 minutes. Make
holes
1-inch
apart in cake.
Pour Jell-O over hot cake; cool 4 hours.
Spread pie filling over cake then Cool Whip.

title: special beef and spinaches
directions: Cut beef in very small pieces and then mix with flavoring, salt, soy sauce and a little fish sauce.
Then take spinaches and put in hot water.
Take them out quickly and cut them shortly. Then set a pan on fire with oil and chop very tiny pieces of garlic and put in it.
Then put in beef that is mixed with ingredients. Blend all together with spinaches.
Add a little water.
Stir 2 or 3 times (not longer) until set.

title: microwave lazy day lasagna
directions: Crumble ground beef into 1 1/2-quart glass casserole. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until no longer pink, stirring once.
Stir to break meat into pieces.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, basil, oregano, garlic powder and water.
Cover with casserole lid.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until mixture boils.

title: pepere's doughnuts
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, shortening and buttermilk. Mix.
Then roll out without too much handling.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Cook in hot fat until golden brown.
Drain and enjoy.

title: chicken creamettes casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, bring to room temperature and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(More chicken may be used.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: angel delight
directions: Break cake into cubes. Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water. Set aside until thick (not stiff). Whip 5 minutes with mixer. Fold in whipped cream, pineapple and nuts. Sprinkle cake cubes in pan. Cover with Jell-O mixture. Chill. Serve.

title: cajun baked potatoes
directions: Quarter each potato on a baking sheet.
Coat with melted butter.
Sprinkle seasonings evenly.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet and add the onion, garlic, paprika and pepper.
Cook until tender, stirring frequently.
Add the bouillon.
Blend the cornstarch in the 1/2 cup water and add to the skillet; stir until smooth.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add the chicken and peas and boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in the yogurt until blended.
Serve over the hot noodles.
Calories per serving:
Fats per serving are less than 20%.

title: watergate fruit salad
directions: Stir pudding mix, pineapple with juice, marshmallows, and nuts in a large bowl until well blended.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery until tender.
Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Mix cornstarch with water, then add to other ingredients.
Crumble crackers on top.
Pour butter over crackers. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix with mixer the first three ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze 1 day.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until foamy.
Add water and vanilla, then flour.
Stir in nuts and gumdrops.
Spread in shallow pan that has been oiled and lightly floured.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.
While warm, leave in pan.
Ice with icing, then cut in oblong strips.

title: challah(jewish new year bread)
directions: Combine water, sugar and yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Stir yeast to dissolve, then let stand until doubled.
Add egg, butter and salt to yeast mixture; whisk until well blended.
Whisk in 1 cup flour for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in remainder to make soft dough, about 1 1/2 cups more.
Knead dough on floured surface, using as much of the remaining flour as needed (to prevent stickiness) until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl; turn dough over to coat.
Let rise, covered, 40 minutes.
Punch dough down; divide into 3 balls, roll into ropes and braid.
Tuck ends under.
Place on a greased pan.
Let raise 20 minutes.

title: misty's favorite carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
In another bowl mix eggs, brown sugar and oil.
Blend in dry ingredients and add carrots, raisins and walnuts.
Spray one 11 x 15-inch baking pan with Pam spray.
Fill pan a little more than 1/2 full with mixture.
Bake at 325° until done, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.
Check with a toothpick.
If it comes out clean, then it's done!

title: cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on cookie pan or sheet into preheated oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Don't dilute.
Mix together orange juice, lemonade, sugar, fruit cocktail, pineapple tidbits, bananas, strawberries and any other kinds of fruit.
Add 7-Up.
Freeze in double cupcake papers or Dixie cups.
Makes 20 full (5 ounce) Dixie cups.
Keeps indefinitely when frozen.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Make a roux of 1/2 cup oil and 1/3 cup flour; brown in skillet until dark.
Set aside.
In a large stew pot, put all vegetables and spices.
Add enough water or chicken broth to cover. Cook until tender. Add roux, shrimp and crab meat. Continue cooking over medium heat 10 minutes.
Serve with cooked rice.
May freeze leftovers.

title: white sauce
directions: Microwave butter at High for 45 to 60 seconds or until melted. Stir in flour and seasonings.
Blend in the milk.
Microwave at High for 4 to 7 minutes or until sauce thickens and bubbles, stirring every minute.

title: ginger carrot bisque
directions: Melt butter in heavy large saucepan over medium heat. Add carrots and onions. Cover saucepan and cook until vegetables begin to soften, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes. Mix in ginger, orange peel, and coriander. Add 2 cups stock. Reduce heat to medium low. Cover pan and simmer soup until carrots are very tender, about 30 minutes. Puree soup in batches in processor or blender. Add remaining 3 cups stock and half & half to soup. Season with salt & pepper. Can be prepared 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Cook over medium heat until warm. Ladle into bowls. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: carrots glazed with orange and ginger
directions: Melt the margarine in a medium-size heavy saucepan.
Add the orange juice, ginger and orange peel; bring to a boil.
Add the carrots and adjust the heat so that the orange juice bubbles gently.
Simmer, uncovered, until all the liquid has evaporated and the carrots are tender and nicely glazed, 10 to 12 minutes. Serves 4.

title: chocolate popcorn
directions: Melt milk confectionary; add peanut butter.
Add to all ingredients and mix until popcorn is coated.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Put in freezer for 5 minutes.
Break apart and it's ready. Store in an airtight container.

title: baked ham in a can
directions: With can opener, make 3 holes in top of can.
Heat can in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour off gelatin.
Combine orange juice, honey, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and mustard.
Pour into can. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix everything together, adding meat last.
Spread on muffins and heat.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles, onion, pepper and celery in broth until tender. Add cut up cheese; stir until it melts.
Add soup and chicken.
Put in large casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: queen of hearts tarts
directions: Simmer fruit with juice in pan.
Add cornstarch and stir until thick.
Pour into pie crust squares and fold.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add finely crushed vanilla wafers alternately with milk. Add coconut and pecans.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: health nut bread
directions: Mix flours, wheat germ, soda, salt and cinnamon.
In another bowl mash bananas; add lemon juice.
In another large bowl mix honey and oil; add eggs and mix.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the buttermilk to honey mixture.
Fold in bananas and rest of fruit and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick in center comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Stir together cranberries, sugar and lemon juice.
Place in baking pan; cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven and stir well.
Mix together orange marmalade and walnuts.
Add to first mixture.
Good with poultry or pork.
Keeps well in refrigerator for weeks.
Can be made well in advance.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli in boiling water until separated.
Drain.
Mix egg, 1/2 can soup (undiluted), mayonnaise and broccoli.
Spread in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes in at 350° oven or until top browns.

title: diabetic fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas; pour pineapple and fruit cocktail over bananas. Do not drain the pineapple and fruit cocktail; use juice. Stir in pudding; mix well. Put in refrigerator until pudding is set.

title: coffee cake
directions: Crumble together first 4 ingredients (save 1 cup for topping). To remaining mixture, mix in eggs, soda, salt and buttermilk. Beat until smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Spoon on any kind of pie filling or jelly.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green chili and cheese appetizer tart
directions: Allow both crusts to stand at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 450°.
Unfold crusts onto ungreased cookie sheet or pizza pan; remove plastic sheets and press out fold lines. Sprinkle cheeses over crust to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Sprinkle with green chiles.
Slightly sprinkle with Crazy Mixed Up salt (use chili powder or seasoned salt instead of Crazy Mixed Up salt for variety).
Seal edges with fork; generously prick top with fork. Sprinkle again with Crazy Mixed Up salt.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes. Cut into wedges and serve with 1 cup of salsa (Rosarita).

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt together candy bars and 1 stick of butter and set aside. Cream together 1 stick of butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour and baking soda.
Add alternately to butter/sugar mixture with buttermilk.
Add the Milky Way mixture and chopped pecans.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa with 1/3 cup milk.
Beat eggs well. Add rest of milk and cook.
When it gets done, add butter and vanilla.

title: velveeta dip
directions: Brown sausage and onion together. Add Velveeta and green tomatoes with chilies and heat over very low heat until cheese is melted. Stir often. Add chili powder. Serve with crackers.

title: savory squash
directions: In a covered saucepan, cook squash and onion in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain well.
Combine with rice, cheese and seasonings.
Blend eggs and mayonnaise together and stir into squash mixture.
Turn into a buttered, shallow, 2-quart casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cut cabbage in half; remove the heart.
Place in large pan of water.
Add 1 tablespoon salt; boil for 15 minutes.
Separate cabbage leaves (they should be bendable but not soft); let cool. Combine in a large bowl the onion salt, garlic powder, ground beef, sausage, eggs, tomato paste and Minute rice (uncooked).
Form a 4-inch (approximate) meatball inside a cabbage leaf.
Roll (tucking in at the sides).
Place in a large saucepan.
When all the cabbage rolls have been placed in saucepan, drain sauerkraut and put it on top of them.
Sprinkle on sugar; pour on tomato juice.
Cook on medium heat for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients and cool.
Mix flour, sugar, eggs, soda, vanilla, buttermilk and salt together; add first mixture. Add all together and mix well. Pour into a large cake pan that is greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix frosting and pour over brownies while warm.

title: chunky tomato soup
directions: Heat oil in 4-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Saute garlic, celery and carrots in oil.
Stir in tomatoes; break up tomatoes coarsely.
Stir in water, broth, basil and pepper and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaves.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Melt butter and remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar and sugar. Allow to cool slightly.
Add beaten eggs, coconut and vanilla. Pour into pie shells.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 30 minutes or until sets.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and bananas together.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Beat again and then stir in nuts. Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lime pepper chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chicken.
Beat with a wire whisk.
Marinate chicken for 1 hour in the refrigerator. Remove and cook the chicken on the grill outside, basting often with the marinade.
Cook meat until done.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Quickly brown chops in oil.
Place in casserole; add in layers onions and peppers.
Mix soup with one can of water and pour over mixture.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: country captain
directions: Wash and cut up chicken ready for cooking.
Put in salt, soda and water.
Let soak in refrigerator overnight.
Take out of water and coat with self-rising flour.
Fry in Crisco oil in deep fryer until golden brown.
Will be crisp and juicy.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients together well and refrigerate.

title: rice meatballs
directions: Combine rice (from box) with beef, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Shape into balls and place in skillet. Add sugar to remaining 2 cups of tomato juice.
Pour over meatballs.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients with fork. Add oil and blend. Sprinkle water over mixture, blend with fork.

title: garlic new potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in lightly salted water about 15 minutes.
Drain and cool. Cut potatoes in quarters and set aside.
Melt butter with oils in large heavy skillet over medium heat. Add potatoes and cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Turn heat up and cook potatoes until golden brown, turning frequently, about 20 minutes. Add garlic, salt, pepper and parsley. Cook for 3 more minutes. Serve hot.

title: lime sherbet molded salad
directions: In large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in sherbet. Cool until syrupy. Spoon whipped topping into large bowl. Gradually beat in jello mixture on low speed until well blended. Pour into a 12-cup mold coated with nonstick cooking spray. Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours until set. Yields 16 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: In a 4 qt. pot, make a roux with the butter and flour over a low heat. Set aside.
In a smaller pot, place in all vegetables. Cover and simmer in small amount of water about 5 mins. Blend & heat chicken broth, Half & Half and milk.
Add this liquid to roux.
Add all vegetables to broth and simmer approx. 45 mins. Brown bacon until crispy.
Crumble and sprinkle in soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Beat over top of a double boiler constantly until it forms a peak.

title: cream corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl, mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 Minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Cover with cheese and crushed crackers.

title: julie's cider
directions: Heat and simmer.
I put it in a large coffee pot after its been heated through.

title: boiled dinner
directions: Boil ham in water for about 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Take out and debone.
Put back in water and add quartered cabbage head.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Take out and add carrots (as many as you please). Cook 15 minutes; take out.
Add as many potatoes as you please. Cook until all is tender.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand, lemon juice and food coloring if desired.
Pour into prepared pastry shell; bake 30 minutes.
Cool.
Chill. Spread with whipped cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: easy pie crust
directions: In a mixing bowl, add water and Crisco.
Cream well.
Add a pinch of salt and then flour.
Mix and roll out on a well-floured board.
Makes 1 pie crust.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: In large saucepan, saute vegetables in margarine for 10 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add the broth and heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Add barley.
Cover and simmer until barley is cooked through (about 1 hour).
Stir in milk, meat, salt and pepper.
Heat through and serve.

title: spicy chicken and pasta
directions: Heat large nonstick skillet (coat with cooking spray).
Add chicken.
Sprinkle with pepper and paprika.
Cook until browned. Stir often.
Remove to plate.
Add onion and 3 tablespoons water to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat until onion wilts.
Add zucchini, green and yellow peppers, garlic and tomatoes with their juices.
Toss with oregano and basil.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 8 minutes.
Return chicken.
Cook another minute. Toss over cooked pasta.

title: chinese pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into large casserole dish. Put 6 raw pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place in a baking dish.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Put 4 handfuls of brown sugar in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add 4 tablespoons butter (room temperature) and enough milk to "cream." Next, flatten 2 loaves frozen white bread dough that have thawed overnight in refrigerator.
Spread with butter.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and chopped pecans.
Roll up like a tootsie roll. Cut roll into about 15 sections.
Place them in rows on top of creamed brown sugar.
Cover and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let cool a little in pan before removing.

title: golden chops with vegetables
directions: Brown pork chops in large nonstick skillet.
Remove pork chops and drain.
Combine soup, water and sage in skillet.
Add carrot and onions.
Arrange pork chops over soup mixture, cover and simmer over medium heat 15 minutes, stirring and rearranging pork chops once.
Add green peppers.
Cover and cook an additional 10 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: e z cake
directions: Grease
and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy broiled zucchini
directions: Place zucchini, cut side up, in a lightly greased broiler pan. Brush tops of zucchini with melted butter and sprinkle with salt, pepper, cheese and paprika.
Broil 6 to 8 inches from heat 12 minutes or until tender.
Yield: 3 servings.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, butter and eggs with vinegar.
Add coconut, raisins and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Cook hen until tender.
Dice chicken and add bread crumbs, rice, salt, pimiento, chicken broth or milk and eggs.
Pack in greased pan and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes.
When done, cut in half.
Remove potatoes from skim, trying not to break skin.
Put potatoes in bowl.
Add salt, pepper, butter, freezer dried chives, Cheddar or Velveeta cheese to taste.
Mix with mixer until smooth and creamy.
Fill potato shells and bake until hot.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In a bowl, drain pineapple; reserve juice in a saucepan.
Mix together juice, 1/2 cup water and lemon juice.
Heat to boiling. Remove from heat and add gelatin, stirring thoroughly.
Break up cranberry sauce with a fork and stir into gelatin mixture. Refrigerate until mixture begins to set.
Stir in pineapple, celery and nuts.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: debbie's orange fluff
directions: Mix together jello, pudding and pie filling; add water.
Bring to a boil and let cool.
Add mandarin oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: drunk chicken
directions: Combine above ingredients and cook on top of stove approximately 30 minutes or until thickened.
Pour into 11 x 13-inch pan.
Add 10 to 12 pieces of chicken.
Bake in 325° oven for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Bring the juice from the crushed pineapple and the Jell-O to a boil.
Add pineapple to your mixture.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Add celery and nuts (optional).
Whip together.
Garnish with pecans.

title: tofu mushrooms
directions: Brown garlic and ginger in butter.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes.
Add tofu.
Garnish with parsley.

title: spinach and gorgonzola pizza
directions: Remove skin from sausage and break into pieces. Fry until cooked.
Remove from frypan, keeping sausage oil in frypan.
Place cooked sausage into a food processor.
Blend.
Return mixture to frypan.
Add spinach and garlic.
Cook until blended.
Remove garlic cloves and set aside.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Cover and chill.
Garnish with red pepper strips.
Serve with raw vegetables.
Yields 1 2/3 cups.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Take out 1 1/2 cups of batter and bake cake as directed.
Cool.
Beat softened cheese; add milk gradually.
Add pudding; beat slowly until dissolved and thick. Spread pineapple over pudding mixture.
Cover top with Cool Whip; sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: home-canned relish(yields approximately 9 pints; consider doubling recipe)
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients. Press out excess liquid before adding salt. Combine all veggies in large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt. Cover with cold water. Let stand 4 hours.
Drain thoroughly. Press out excess liquid.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Mix lemon jello, sugar, hot water and lemon and chill about 1/2 hour.
Chill the evaporated milk 1/2 hour also.
Whip each separately and then whip them together.
Put graham cracker crumbs on top and bottom.

title: butterscotch bubble bread
directions: Butter pan.
Dump in frozen rolls.
Add dry pudding mix, brown sugar and nuts in small bowl.
Scatter over dough.
It will sift down between rolls as they thaw and raise.
Cut margarine into thin pats.
Arrange over the top of rolls in pan.
Cover and leave until morning (they will rise).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in center of oven for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and
eggs.
Add applesauce; mix well. Stir in sifted dry ingredients, alternately with water. Blend fruits and nuts into
the
batter.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Frost with Penuche Frosting.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease large glass baking dish with butter.
Arrange shrimp in a single layer in baking dish.
Evenly sprinkle parsley and cheese over shrimp.
Chop garlic and distribute evenly over shrimp.
Cut butter into pieces and put on shrimp.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry blossoms
directions: Remove stems from berries to form a flat base.
Place on a cutting surface, pointed end up.
With a sharp knife, carefully slice each berry in half vertically to within 1/4 inch of base. Cut each half into 3 wedges to form 6 petals.
(Do not slice through base.)
Pull petals slightly apart; then in a small bowl beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and sour cream until fluffy. With a small spoon, fill strawberries.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: egg rolls
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients in large bowl.
Drain excess liquid.
Spoon approximately 3 tablespoons of filling in center of wrap.
Fold bottom and top edges up just to cover edge of filling. Fold sides over, moistening edges to seal.
Deep fry a few rolls at a time in hot oil at medium heat (375°) until golden (about 3 minutes).
Drain excess oil.
Serve immediately with soy sauce, duck sauce, etc.

title: minnie's rolled sweet potatoes
directions: Thoroughly mash potatoes.
Add all ingredients, except shortening or oil and corn flakes.
Take serving spoon of mixture and shape into potato shape.
Roll in crushed corn flakes.
Place in baking pan with oil.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: robert makes pancakes
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Beat until well blended (that's the fun part!).
Let dad cook them.
Makes 12 pancakes.

title: chicken ole
directions: In a small bowl, blend together soup, sour cream, milk and chicken broth.
Set aside.
Break tortillas into pieces and place in a casserole dish, then add chicken, green chiles and soup mixture; repeat.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine cucumbers and onions.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Blend all the rest of ingredients.
Boil for 8 minutes.
Place in hot jars and seal.

title: frozen rocky road squares
directions: Combine flour, butter and 1/2 cup chopped pecans; press into bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: cinnamon biscuit fans
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 8 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch.
Cut 1/3 cup margarine into flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, the baking powder and salt with pastry blender in large bowl until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in just enough milk so dough leaves side of bowl and forms a ball.

title: orange dessert salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sherbet and mix well. When partially set, add whipped cream.
Chill; sets quickly.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients in a bowl and spread over chicken in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Note:
This recipe doubled makes about 50 cookies.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Saute onions and celery in butter. Combine with cooked rice and all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cherry pie
directions: With pastry blender, combine flour, margarine, brown sugar and oatmeal.
Save out 1 cup.
Place rest of mixture in 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Press on sides and bottom of pie plate to form crust. Pour in cherry (or blueberry) filling.
Sprinkle rest of crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian eggplant parmigiana
directions: Wash eggplant and cut into slices 1/4-inch thick; do not peel. Season with salt and pepper.
Dip into bread crumbs.
Dip into eggs and then again in bread crumbs (may need more eggs and crumbs). Place in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Fry eggplant slices until tender and golden.
Brown on both sides.
Add more oil when needed. Drain on paper towels.
Line a buttered baking dish with some sauce.
Arrange a single layer of eggplant on sauce.
Cover with Mozzarella, sauce, basil and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry bread
directions: Mix flour, soda and baking powder.
Add cherries, chocolate chips, dates and nuts.
Set aside.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and herbs; mix well.
Dip chicken into melted margarine and then bread crumbs to coat.
Place on baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together last four ingredients.
Cut broccoli to desired size and place in bowl.
Crumble bacon on top.
Pour mayonnaise mixture over broccoli.
Refrigerate.
Can be made the night before.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, nutmeg, cream of tartar and boiling water. Cook to 246° on candy thermometer. Add vanilla and walnut halves. Stir until nuts are completely covered. Turn onto greased cookie sheet. Separate with two forks while hot. Cool. Makes 3 cups.

title: ham rolls
directions: Cut ham very thin.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Soften cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Season highly with prepared mustard and onion juice to taste.
Spread on ham squares.
Roll tightly and serve on toothpick.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Use powdered sugar on hands to push out dough.
Bake until brown.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar; spread over dough.
Spread strawberries over cream cheese.
Spread glaze over strawberries.
Add whipped cream when ready to eat.
Decorate with strawberries.

title: shrimp, steak and chicken stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry meats in oil, seasoning with garlic and seasoning salt; set aside.
Stir-fry vegetables until done.
Add garlic. Mix cornstarch and water well; mix into vegetables.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Soak cabbage in bowl of cold water 10 minutes; drain well. If not already shredded, cut cabbage into 1/8-inch wide shreds. Squeeze dry between paper toweling.

title: sunshine macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, cheese, celery, ham and onion. Add enough salad dressing to moisten. Mix well. Chill. Serves 6.

title: "wrapping paper" stickers
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young.
When selected, give your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some wives insist upon keeping them in a pickle.
Others are constantly getting them into hot water.
This may make them sour, hard, and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be sweet, tender and good, by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with love and seasoned with kisses.
Wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
Serves 2.

title: potato and pepper casserole
directions: Place slices of the cooked potatoes into a casserole dish. Add the onion and green peppers into the white sauce.
Pour over the potatoes.
Sprinkle the cheese on top and allow to sink in. Place in a 350° oven for about 1/2 hour.
Serves 6.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Boil water; add sugar and coffee.
Before it cools, add the vanilla.
Cool and add the vodka.
Seal in glass jars for 2 weeks before serving.
Keeps for a long time.

title: tofu mayonnaise
directions: In food processor or blender, combine all ingredients, except oil, until smooth.
With motor running, slowly drizzle oil through feed tube until mixture is creamy.
Refrigerate in a covered container (mixture thickens when chilled).

title: scripture cake
directions: After following instructions in Proverbs 23:14, pour batter into well-greased loaf pans and bake for 50 minutes in preheated 325° oven.
Cool and slice after a few John 11:9.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles; drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine cottage cheese with eggs, seasonings and Parmesan cheese.
Place 1/2 noodles in a 13 x 9-inch pan, spread 1/2 cottage cheese mixture over, then 1/2 the Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 the meat.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with triangles of Mozzarella.
Let stand a few minutes until filling is slightly set.
Serves 8 generously or 12 smaller.

title: curry sauced cauliflower
directions: In a covered skillet over medium heat, in 1/2-inch boiling water, cook cauliflower for 5 minutes or until tender-crisp. Drain in colander.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Season chicken lightly with salt and pepper.
In large skillet over medium heat, melt butter.
Add chicken.
Cook 5 minutes on each side or until browned, turning once.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Stir onion into skillet.
Sprinkle flour, paprika and dill evenly on top.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes; stir in broth and water. Return chicken to skillet; reduce heat to medium.
Cook uncovered 15 to 20 minutes until chicken is cooked through and juices are slightly reduced.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream alternative until well blended.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over noodles.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix together; drop from spoon.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes, gradually adding sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix dry ingredients; fold into pumpkin mixture. Spread into well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with nuts. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on wax paper that has been liberally dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll.
Cool and unroll. Spread with filling.

title: saturday's chicken
directions: Mix soup and cream.
Lay chicken in oiled 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and pour cream and soup over it.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°, uncovered.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Chill pared potatoes in ice water for 2 hours before grating. Finely grate potatoes and measure 2 cups full.
Place grated potatoes in towel and squeeze out water.
Combine potatoes, eggs, flour, baking powder and salt. Drop by tablespoon onto hot, well-greased griddle. Cook over moderate heat about 5 minutes on each side, until golden brown.
Makes eight 3-inch pancakes.

title: pineapple dream pie
directions: Drain the pineapple.
Mix the Cool Whip and milk together. Add lemon juice, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.

title: hamburger balls
directions: Mix hamburger, rice and onion together. Shape into balls the size of walnuts and put in baking pan or dish. Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over balls. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: Sift together the first 6 ingredients in large mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer.
Bake in greased and lightly floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan in moderate oven (350°) for about 35 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill for at least 6 hours.
Serve with Hawaiian bread.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: jelly roll cake
directions: Beat eggs well until light and thick.
Add sugar gradually and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Add water and mix.
Spread in a small cookie (10 x 13 x 15-inch) sheet and bake at 325° for 20 minutes or lightly brown.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and mix at high speed until smooth. Use this in any recipe that calls for Eagle Brand milk. Makes 14 ounces.

title: eclaire dessert(no bake)
directions: Mix instant pudding with milk.
Leave about 5 minutes to set. Then fold in Cool Whip.
Layer 9 x 13 pan with whole graham crackers, then pour 1/2 of the pudding mix on top of crackers. Then put another layer of crackers on top.
Then put remaining pudding mixture on top.
Top with a layer of crackers and frost with chocolate frosting.
Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all together, pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chinese slaw
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add noodles and cashews before serving.
Mix together.
Keep cool.

title: shrimp supreme
directions: Combine all the ingredients except the shrimp.
Place crisp lettuce on a platter or individual plates.
Add the shrimp and toss lightly.
Refrigerate the salad until you are ready to serve.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise.
Parboil 25 minutes.
Cool and scoop out pulp to 1/4-inch of skin.
Cut pulp in cubes.
Melt butter or margarine in medium skillet.
Add garlic, celery, carrots and onion.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Blend in eggplant pulp and other ingredients.
Spoon mixture into eggplant shell.
Place in buttered baking dish and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: blue cheese burgers
directions: Prepare grill.
Blend Blue cheese, garlic, parsley, club soda, pepper and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add ground beef; mix everything lightly but completely.
Shape into approximately 8 patties.
Grill burgers for 2 to 3 minutes on each side for medium rare, or until desired.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash beans and add all ingredients except parsley, sausage and rice.
Cover with water.
(You can add more water later.)
You want the beans to make a thick gravy.
Cook covered until beans are done.
Add sausage and parsley and cook 15 to 20 minutes longer. Serve over hot rice.

title: chocolate gooey bars
directions: Heat butter until melted.
Sprinkle and
pat cake mix over it. Sprinkle with marshmallows, chocolate chips and cereal.
Drizzle milk over top.
Bake for time set or until cereal is golden brown (350° for 20 to 25 minutes).
While warm run knife around edge.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies in 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool. Break into pieces. Place 1/2 in the bottom of a trifle dish. Put mousse over brownies. Sprinkle with 1/2 crushed Heath bars. Top with Cool Whip. Repeat layers. Sprinkle mini chocolate chips on the top.

title: foamy pudding sauce
directions: Beat egg whites dry, adding a little sugar when beaten stiff, and continue beating until thick.
Add remaining sugar to yolks and beat.
Add 2 tablespoons boiling water to yolks and continue beating well.
Add to beaten whites and beat until smooth.
Add flavoring of 1 teaspoon vanilla or 1/4 cup of brandy.
Beat enough to mix.
Serve on pudding.

title: dump cake
directions: In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread pie filling on bottom of pan.
Spread pineapple over cherries.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Pour melted butter over cake mix, and add nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Leave in pan.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: vegetable jello mold
directions: Combine sliced vegetables in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix jello.
Use less water and let gel slightly.
Add vegetables, onion and vinegar to slightly gelled jello.
Let gel until firm.
Serve on lettuce.
Top with mayonnaise as desired.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil in 1-quart Pyrex measure, then cook for 2 minutes on Full power.
Remove and add baking soda.
Stir well.
Spray inside of large brown grocery bag. Pour popcorn into it.
Pour syrup over corn; stir.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes on Full power.
Take out and shake bag well.
Return and cook 1 1/2 minutes more on Full power.
Open bag and cool.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and pat into rectangular cake pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Cool and top with these three layers.

title: corn and zucchini soup
directions: Saute onion and zucchini in oil until soft.
Stir in chicken broth, water, corn and oregano.
Chop apple into small chunks and add to mixture.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve piping hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, picante and chili powder together. Use 1 cup of soup mixture and mix with chicken and cheese. Warm up tortillas and spread about 1/4 cup chicken/cheese/soup mixture per tortilla. Roll up and place seam side down in 3-quart baking dish. Pour remaining soup mixture on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and add drained, diced tomatoes. Cook for 10 minutes. Garnish with sliced green onion(s) before serving. (Baking time may vary from 30 to 40 minutes.)

title: super skillet meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, salt and garlic powder; shape into meatballs.
Brown in oil or melted margarine; drain.
Mix tomato sauce, water, basil, salt and pepper; pour over meatballs.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked and drained noodles.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake until golden brown at 400° or 500°.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Place prunes and apricots in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients, spoon over dried fruit.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 12 servings.

title: salmon party spread
directions: Drain salmon; mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate. Form into a ball or loaf.
Cover with chopped pecans.
Serve cold with crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top with some grated cheese. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: flan
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Set aside.
Melt 1/2 cup of sugar in a pie pan.
Allow to cool.
Add mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until
firm and golden brown.

title: crab and corn bisque
directions: Saute celery, onions, pepper and butter in a Dutch oven.
Add soup and next 8 ingredients.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in crab meat gently.
Heat thoroughly on medium/low heat.

title: cheese quick bread
directions: Blend first four ingredients until smooth.
Stir in remaining until moist.
Pour mix into a greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter until translucent.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes on low heat.
Will keep in refrigerator for a month.
Good sauce for chicken, ribs or barbecued oysters.

title: easy sweet and sour pork
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Add pea pods, mushrooms, pepper and onions.
Stir-fry 3 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Add remaining oil with pork; cook for 5 minutes.
Add vegetables and sauces, heating thoroughly.
Serve over hot rice.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix all together and cook over medium heat until thick. Cool. Add a few drops red coloring.

title: baked sea trout
directions: Cut filets into serving size portions.
Place in a single layer, skin side down, in a well-greased baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over fish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Serves 6.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix together.
Use as a sauce for cold roast beef sandwiches, on hamburgers, or for dipping cheese or ring bologna.

title: nut cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, salt and sugar into large bowl. Add shortening, milk,
vanilla and almond extract.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add
eggs
and
extra yolk all at once to mixture.
Beat 2 minutes
longer. Line well greased and lightly floured
10-inch
tube
pan
with	chopped
nuts
and cherries. Add batter.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: verne's quick buttermilk pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat on medium speed until creamy and well mixed (about 10 minutes).
Pour into prepared tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: curry chicken
directions: Heat vegetable oil in pan.
Chop chicken into pieces and add to pan with salt. Let chicken brown, then add curry powder, m.s.g. and cumin.
Let it cook for 5 minutes.
Add water. Cover pan and let it cook until gravy is thick.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Grease one (8 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pan.
Mix peanut butter and margarine until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; mix with sugar.
Add to peanut butter mixture; work in with spoon or fork until fine crumbs form.
Add lemon rind.
Mix eggs and milk; add to flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes, or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in the pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: peggy's dip(everyone's favorite)
directions: You also need 1 pie plate or quiche plate.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan and stir with a fork until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: zesty baked chicken
directions: Combine first three ingredients, sprinkle over both sides of chicken.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine 1/4 cup yogurt and soy sauce, brush half over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Turn chicken over, brush with remaining yogurt/soy sauce mixture.
Bake additional 10 minutes.
Combine 1/2 cup yogurt and flour, stir well, spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese, bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 teaspoon of sugar and 3/4 cup water.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream together eggs, softened margarine and sugar.
Add bananas.
In another bowl, sift together flour, salt and soda. Add flour mixture a little at a time to sugar and butter mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in nuts and add vanilla. Pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan or small loaf pans.
In large pan bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chinese sweet 'n sour ravioli
directions: Saute luncheon meat and onions in margarine.
Drain syrup from canned pineapple.
Stir 1/2 cup pineapple syrup into meat-onion mixture along with brown sugar and vinegar.
Bring to boil.
Add mini ravioli.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Top with pineapple slices and prunes.
Simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serves four.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Lightly brown hamburger; cover with water.
Add chopped cabbage, sliced carrots, onions, tomatoes and sauce.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add potatoes and seasonings.
Continue cooking until potatoes are tender.
(A good substitute for tomatoes is stewed tomatoes.)

title: cinnamon crisps
directions: Layer graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Melt butter and margarine with sugar.
Pour over cookies.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until bubbling.
Cool slightly; remove onto wire rack.

title: chicken vesuvio
directions: Slice onion.
Peel potatoes and parboil for 15 minutes.
Saute chicken, garlic and onion in 1/4 cup of oil.
Add potatoes and 1/4 cup of oil (quarter potatoes).
Sprinkle rosemary over chicken and potatoes.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Turn potatoes and chicken. Cook an additional 15 minutes until chicken and potatoes are golden brown.

title: mexican cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray two baking sheets with nonstick cooking spray.
Brush both sides of each tortilla with water.
Cut each one into 6 triangles and place in large bowl.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle mixture over triangles and toss to coat pieces well.

title: fudge toffee
directions: Stir until dissolved, then boil 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Have ready the chopped walnuts in bottom of buttered pan. Pour mixture over top.
Put chocolate chips over top and let melt, then spread and cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bring chicken to a boil and simmer for 1 hour (add salt to water, if desired).
Cook broccoli as directed and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Break cooked chicken in pieces and place on top of broccoli.
Combine sour cream and soup; spread over top. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Cool.
Add marshmallows and 1/4 cup coconut; mix.
Sprinkle rest of coconut on a piece of foil and roll the chocolate and marshmallow mixture in the coconut.
Make into a log-like roll on waxed paper.
Refrigerate and slice.

title: banana fruit cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar, eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend into other mixture.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with boiling water.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into mold.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine egg yolks, vinegar and sugar.
Stir while cooking over low-medium heat.
While this is hot, melt marshmallows.
Add the pineapple, chopped peaches, chopped cherries and pecans.
Whip the whipping cream and add.
(Do not use Cool Whip.)
Refrigerate overnight.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine milk and pudding mix in a medium bowl; stir with a wire whisk 2 minutes or until thickened.
Add yogurt and orange juice concentrate; stir well.
Combine apples and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add pudding mixture, stirring gently to coat.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.
Sprinkle with shredded coconut.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken and cut up. Mix soup, sour cream and chicken. Pour into casserole dish. Mix cracker crumbs, poppy seeds and melted margarine. Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy made peach cobbler
directions: Note:
Unsweetened peaches and Equal can be used if diabetic.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Roast spareribs in very hot 500° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Reduce heat to moderate (325°).
Roast 1 1/2 hours, basting every 15 minutes with sauce made by mixing remaining ingredients.
Serve with Barbecue Sauce.

title: favorite cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients with butter, milk and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Fill 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each until light and fluffy.
Add oil, vanilla and lemon zest and beat until mixed well.
Sift the four dry ingredients. Gradually add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture and beat until well blended.
Chill.
On greased cookie sheet, form heaping teaspoonfuls into ball.
Flatten with fork or use cookie press. Bake for 10 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: beef stuff
directions: Mix all this up and put in a 2-quart casserole dish and cover tightly.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Do not peek.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make well in center. Mix remaining ingredients and pour into well.
Mix just enough to dampen all ingredients and pour into greased loaf pan.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake 1 hour at 350.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften and mix ingredients (except Mexican cheese, chopped lettuce and tomatoes) together. Put in dish and top with grated Mexican cheese and chopped lettuce and tomatoes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt oleo in a large pan.
Add marshmallows and melt while stirring constantly.
Add food coloring and mix well. Add corn flakes, a cup or so at a time.
Stir until flakes are well coated. Spoon onto waxed paper quickly and decorate with candy red hots immediately, while still hot.
You may have to reheat mixture on low heat from time to time because it must be hot enough for candies to stick and pliable in order to drop onto waxed paper.

title: dark fruitcake(mom slate, 1970)
directions: *Dredge in flour to prevent settling.

title: "hello dollies"
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° if glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts. Press down gently.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.
Makes 24 bars.

title: *kadaifi rolls 3
directions: One hour before you start, roll the kataifi up in a moist towel.
(This softens the kataifi and allows you to work it easier.)
Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine walnuts, cinnamon, nutmeg, sugar and egg.
Divide kataifi into 4 long sections.
Cut each piece in half (8 pieces).
Flatten each piece to a 3 x 6-inch rectangle.
Spoon a little melted butter evenly on the rectangle.
Place 1 tablespoon of the walnut mixture at one end.
Roll up "jelly roll" fashion.
Place, seam side down, onto a greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle the Kadaifi Rolls with a little water before baking.
Pour a little syrup slowly on the kadaifi.

title: hot hominy
directions: On medium heat, put butter and chili powder in iron skillet. Add hominy and onion; cook until dry.
Add picante sauce and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and lay cheese slices over the top.
When cheese is melted, stir into hominy.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Take lasagna noodles and put in big pot on medium-high to boil with 1 teaspoon of oil.
Then fry hamburger meat until done. Drain excess fat from meat.
When noodles are done, drain water, then put noodles first in a large casserole dish, then put hamburger meat and spaghetti sauce.
Put Cheddar cheese, then Mozzarella on top of it. Then you continue to layer with noodles, meat, mushrooms, cheese, sauce and minced onions.
(This should come out with hamburger meat on top.)
Then put Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese on top of meat, then put the remaining Ragu sauce on top of cheese with a few sprinkles of Parmesan cheese.
Bake in oven for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cook until brown on top and mostly all cheeses have melted throughout lasagna.
Let it cool for 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter in frying pan; add dry ingredients, which have been mixed.
Then add egg yolks and milk, which have been mixed. Bring to low boil, then add vanilla; stir until it becomes thick. Pour into browned pie shells.
Top with egg whites.

title: chinese style wing flings
directions: Mix sugar, soy sauce and oil in a large pot.
Add chicken and stir so that chicken is covered with sauce.
Bring to a boil. Reduce to medium heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle some coconut on top. Makes large amount.

title: meatballs and mushrooms
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, onion,
bread cubes and salt and pepper to taste.
Make into meatballs and brown.
Put in casserole dish.
Add mushroom soup, milk (enough to cover meatballs) and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve mushroom gravy over mashed potatoes.

title: rich peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch square pan.
Stir together flour, 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk.
Pour into pan of butter, but do not mix.
Mix peaches with 1/2 cup sugar and drop over the batter, but do not mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Number 1 Mix:
Mix egg, shortening, sugar, applesauce, salt and spices.

title: homemade pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Put in jars and hot water bath for 20 minutes or freeze.

title: best baked beans
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; lay bacon on top.
Bake at 325° uncovered for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops in electric skillet; remove from skillet.
Place rice, water, bouillon, butter and pepper in skillet.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter or margarine and peanut butter together.
Add sugars, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add gradually to creamed mixture. Stir in Kroger peanut butter chips.
(Now you have the recipe for these cookies!)
Form dough into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly with a fork.
Bake for 9 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Allow to cool for a minute, then remove from cookie sheet.
Yield:
approximately 60 (2-inch) cookies.

title: breakfast before
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Remove crust from bread; cube and coat in oleo.
Place bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble sausage next, then top with cheese.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mozzarella fritters
directions: Cut Mozzarella into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Mix flour, paprika, salt and pepper in a shallow dish.
Put eggs into a second dish and bread crumbs into a third.
Coat cheese cubes lightly in seasoned flour.
Dip into eggs, then into bread crumbs to coat evenly.
Repeat once more with eggs and bread crumbs.
Preheat oil to 350°.
Fry cubes about 2 minutes.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer to paper towel to drain.
Serve hot.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Cut up into small pieces.
Cook spaghetti in chicken stock left from boiling chicken.
Saute chopped onion, chopped bell pepper and chopped celery in a skillet until tender.
Add all ingredients together well.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: lemon cake pie or sponge
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients; add the yolks, grated rind and juice, then add the milk.
Beat the 2 egg whites stiff and fold in.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes. Makes 1 large pie.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Cream together, butter, sugar and egg.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon; add to butter mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in a greased 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked stuffed fish
directions: In a bowl, mash scallops with a potato masher.
Add cracker crumbs and Parmesan cheese and stir.
In a baking pan, lay fish flat.
Lightly brush on melted butter.
Spread mixture on fish and roll.
Brush on melted butter and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Sift flour.
Start with 1 cup flour. Mix, then add 3 eggs and mix.
Continue adding flour and eggs, beating after each addition, ending with flour.
Add milk accordingly.
Then add vanilla and mix.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan that is greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: ladyfinger cake
directions: Line a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers (bottom and sides).
Beat cheese and add vanilla and powdered sugar.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put pineapple and dry pudding mix into bowl; mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put into refrigerator until cool.

title: corn pops
directions: Pour puffed corn in a large paper bag.
Boil corn syrup, sugar and margarine.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and soda.
Pour onto corn and shake.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Shake vigorously!
Microwave again again 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Shake again.
Dump onto waxed paper and cool.

title: mixed pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers in 2-inch sticks.
Cover with salt brine (1/2 cup salt to 1 quart water).
Let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Pare carrots; cut in 2-inch sticks.
Cook in small amount of boiling water for 5 minutes.
Remove seeds from peppers; cut in sticks.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables. Heat just to boiling.
Seal in hot jars.
Makes 8 pints.
Small onions cooked in water until just tender may be used.
Use as many as you like.

title: senator wallop's birthday torte(white chocolate mousse torte)
directions: Butter 10-inch diameter spring-form pan with 2 3/4-inch high sides.
Finely grind cookies in processor.
Add melted butter and blend until combined.
Press crust mixture onto bottom (not sides) of pan.
Bring cream to a simmer in heavy medium saucepan. Reduce heat to low.
Add chocolate and whisk until melted and smooth.
Pour chocolate mixture over crust.
Chill.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until it springs back to touch.

title: fresh mushroom dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and seasonings.
Fold in sour cream and chill.
Stir in mushrooms just before serving.

title: raised waffles
directions: Scald milk.
Add salt and butter.
When lukewarm, add yeast dissolved in water, and then flour.
Beat well.
Let rise overnight.
Add yolks well beaten, and egg whites beaten stiff. Cook in hot waffle iron.
Serves 4.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix soy sauce, garlic salt and lemon pepper in zipper bag. Add meat; marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Place in single layer on cookie sheet.
Bake at 200° for 10 to 12 hours.
Store in airtight container.

title: crumb topping for pies
directions: Let butter soften and then add all ingredients together. Using a fork, cut into mixture until crumbly.
Sprinkle over pie.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, vanilla and oil. Blend well. Add zucchini and all dry ingredients. Mix well. Fold in nuts and raisins. Turn into 2 greased and floured bread pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine in pan the first four ingredients and bring to a boil. Boil for at least 3 minutes. After removing from the heat, add the next 3 ingredients.

title: apple praline pie
directions: Bake your favorite apple pie.
Remove from oven.

title: rolls
directions: Sift flour and sugar in bowl; mix well.
Mix in egg, oil and milk.
Fill cupcake pan 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: I had this for dessert five nights in a row at Mick's, a great restaurant in Decatur, Georgia.

As soon as I got home, I dragged out my National Grange cookbook, and recreated this wonderful dessert for some friends, who promptly declared it "illegal north of the Mason-Dixon Line" and polished it off!
The cheesecake is from the National Grange cookbook (a recipe by Julieann Smith, West Bridgewater Grange, MA), but the construction is mine.
(Nanette P. Benoit/DeGraw).

title: italian sausages and potatoes
directions: Place all ingredients in roasting pan.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, oil and oregano.
Stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring a couple of time.

title: chile cheese bean dip
directions: Cook hamburger meat.
Remove grease.
Add 1/2 package taco seasoning with 1/4 cup water.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Crumble meat into small pieces; let stand.
Melt Velveeta cheese with butter. Add 1 cup mild taco sauce, green chiles, hamburger mixture and refried beans.
Mix well.
Keep warm.
Serve with chips.
Flavor improves the longer dip sits.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk; boil 5 1/2 minutes.
Put chocolate in double boiler and melt before adding to first mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and pour.
Makes 5 1/2 pounds of delicious fudge.

title: old fashioned cabbage dinner
directions: Saute onions, garlic and pepper in fat for 20 minutes.
Add seasoning with chopped meat.
Pour into a large pot.
Add corn, tomatoes and sauce or puree.
Pour in bottom of pan (13 x 9-inch) and mix corn meal your usual way and drop by spoon in top of mixture.
Bake in hot oven for 30 minutes.
Can sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.

title: omelet popover(sweden)
directions: Beat eggs lightly in bowl.
Add flour and salt; mix until smooth.
Stir in milk gradually.
Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Pour into batter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let stand until slightly cooled and butter is absorbed.
Serve with legon. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: biscuits
directions: Cut
shortening into dry ingredients.
Add milk to form ball. Knead
until smooth.
Bake at 400° on greased pan until lightly brown.

title: plum good cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and plums.
Sift flour, cinnamon and cloves.
Add the two mixtures together; then add vanilla, raisins, nuts and coconut.
Bake in a well-greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: haystacks
directions: Prepare hamburger sauce by browning hamburger with onion.
Add taco seasoning, tomato juice and water. Simmer 15 minutes. Serve in dishes individually in the following order:
crackers, rice, hamburger sauce, taco chips, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese sauce, Cheddar cheese and olives.
To form haystacks, layer each portion, forming a mound on your plate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: norwegian gold cake
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese until smooth. Gradually add sugar, beating until light.
