Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition (very important).
Then beat in flour and vanilla two minutes or until smooth.
Pour into buttered and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 375° for one hour or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Needs no frosting.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar as an option.

title: corn beef ball
directions: Mix well and shape into a ball.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: sourdough coffee cake
directions: Mix and pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: red clam sauce
directions: Cook onion in heated oil until soft.
Add tomatoes, paste, basil, garlic and pepper to taste and simmer for 30 minutes, sirring occasionally.
Add the clams and enough broth to flavor the sauce without making it too thin.
Taste and adjust seasoning by adding pepper, salt or a pinch of sugar.
Simmer 15 minutes more.
Serve hot over linguini, spaghetti or capellini.

title: meat smoke seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and store in airtight container. Rub a small amount of mixture over entire outer surface of brisket, turkey, etc., before smoking in standard or water smoker.
One tablespoon is plenty for average size Thanksgiving turkey.
Makes about 1 pound of seasoning.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over meatballs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Use 1 (10-inch) pie shell, cooled.
In mixing bowl, combine powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Knead until like cottage cheese.
Set aside.
Separate eggs, saving whites.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: green chili quiche
directions: Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Spread chilies in pan and sprinkle with cheese.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve on club crackers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries oranges, and apples fine. Add pineapple and juice set aside. Mix jellos with 4 cups boiling water and 4 cups sugar. Stir until dissolved, then add all other ingredients - will make a gallon.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Crumble one slice of bread on top and grated cheese if desired.

title: pasta with mushrooms
directions: Pour olive oil into skillet; add garlic and heat.
Add mushrooms and saute until pale brown and give up their juices. Sprinkle with lots of chopped chives and pour over 1 pound cooked, drained pasta.
Salt and pepper at table.

title: dang good pie
directions: Mix all together, and bake in pie shell at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla. Stir until mixed.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
(Do not overcook.)

title: tuna ball(club member: lee ann mcraney)
directions: Combine tuna, cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and smoke in a bowl. Roll in ball. Cover in crushed pecans. Chill and serve on crackers.

title: swiss almond dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread in a 9-inch serving/baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, stirring after 8 minutes. Garnish with additional almonds, if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: egg and sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Lay buttered bread, butter side down, into oblong casserole dish and cut into pieces.
Put sausage (fried) on top.
Add shredded cheese.
Mix together on top.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard together.
Pour over bread mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add spices. Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased pans.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump in the can of crushed undrained pineapple.
Dump cherry pie filling on top of pineapple. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
(Do not mix.) Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Slice butter into thin pieces and place on top. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: lace cookies
directions: Combine first four ingredients and mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon 3 inches apart onto aluminum foil-lined cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are brown.
Cool completely before removing.
Yields at least 6 1/2 dozen.

title: garlic cheese roll
directions: Mix ingredients together well and roll in logs or balls.
Roll in paprika or chili powder and store in waxed paper in refrigerator.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix all together (potatoes still frozen).
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with another cup of grated Cheddar cheese or melt 2 teaspoons of butter and mix with 1 cup Special K (slightly crumbled).
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each.
Add cocoa, flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cattleman's cafe salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Keep refrigerated.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, butter (or oleo) and salt.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly over moderate heat.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and nuts; stir well until chips are melted.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan (with oleo).
Chill in refrigerator until firm, about 2 hours.
Yield:
2 1/4 pounds.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk. Set aside.
Mix remaining milk, cake mix and margarine together. Press
half of cake mixture onto bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake	8
minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate bits and 1 cup	nuts over
crust; top with caramel mixture, spreading to edges.	Top with
teaspoons
of remaining cake mixture; press gently
into caramel
mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts. Bake 16 to 18 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until tender; chop.
Mix remaining ingredients, except potato chips.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Crumble chips; place on top of casserole. Bake 5 more minutes.

title: new year's day bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain liquid.
Add salt, ham and peppers; cook over medium heat until tender.
Add lemon and brown sugar.

title: apple drink
directions: Cook sugar and water with cinnamon, cloves, etc.
Peel and quarter apples.
Put into the boiling water (syrup).
When fruit is soft, cool.
Serve cold.

title: diet cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and sift.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into small loaf pan and bake at 325° until done.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets until tender, leaving about 2-inches of stem to prevent bleeding.
Prepare spiced vinegar as follows: vinegar, water and sugar.
Mix together.
Let boil about 2 minutes.
Tie bags of mixed pickle spices for each jar.
Remove skim from beets; drop into mixture.
Put in a slice lemon and bring to boiling point.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients in a casserole dish in the order listed. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and serve immediately.
Does not keep well.

title: apricot kolachky(slovak cookies)
directions: Mix the butter or oleo with the cream cheese until smooth and creamy.
Add the flour.

Mix with your hands, until well blended. Roll the dough to about 1/8-inch thick; cut in 3-inch squares. Place about 1/2 teaspoon of apricot filling in center of square. Press together 2 opposite corners tightly, or any other shape. Bake at 350° for about 18 minutes.
Cool, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Can be frozen.

title: pecan custard
directions: First mix the flour with 1 cup sugar and then cream the butter with the second cup of sugar.
Add the well beaten yolks of egg, the beaten whites, flour and sugar.
Add the milk and lastly, the nuts.
Mix all well together.
Pour into a well buttered baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Custard may be served hot or cold with whipped cream.

title: creole salad dressing
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in vinegar; then add olive oil and garlic. Shake well until emulsified.
Sprinkle lightly over lettuce or any salad you prefer.
Season salad with Tony's Creole seasoning to taste.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine.
Melt margarine in deep dish.
Pour batter in dish.
Spoon peaches and juice over entire dish.
Do not stir.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: artichoke pizza
directions: Unroll dough without tearing and press into a 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until cooked through. Combine remaining ingredients, saving 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese to sprinkle on top.
Spread on crust.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 36.

title: lollipop cookies(for kids)
directions: Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: milk nut fudge
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, mix sugar, butter or margarine, marshmallows and milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils and is bubbly all over top.
Boil and stir for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate morsels until melted.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut into about 30 pieces.

title: nachos
directions: Layer chips on cookie sheet.
Brown hamburger, add taco mix and a little water to blend.
Sprinkle over chips.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° until cheese is melted.
Serve with lettuce, sour cream, tomatoes and salsa.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Bake in 2 x 9 x 10-inch Pyrex or pan at 350° until brown.

title: "copper pennies" or marinated carrots
directions: After cooking carrots, drain water off.
Add all ingredients (already combined) to them while hot.
Will keep for days.

title: carrot salad(low calorie)
directions: Combine orange juice and mustard in a small bowl for dressing. In a large bowl combine carrots, apples and cranberries. Pour the dressing over the ingredients in the large bowl. Toss well, cover and refrigerate until chilled. Best served the same day - does not hold over well. Serves 2.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, peppers and onion.
Sprinkle with turmeric. Dissolve salt in water.
Pour salt water over vegetable mixture. Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain.
Cover with cold water 1 hour. Drain thoroughly.

title: lobster mousse "cape cod"
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese until cream cheese is melted.
Stir in milk, lobster meat, celery, onion, garlic, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add to mixture.
Pour into greased mold or shaped glass or plastic dish. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Unmold, if desired.
Serve on a bed of shredded romaine and arrange radishes, carrots, broccoli and cauliflower around mousse.
Garnish with cilantro.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Mix in order given.
Sift all dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add oats last.
Form three rolls on separate sheets of waxed paper.
Chill at least 24 hours.
Cut 1/4-inch slices and bake at 350°.
These can be drop cookies.

title: uncle chip's world famous chili
directions: Brown bacon, sausage and ground beef; drain.
Cook onion, bell pepper and butter over low heat.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce. Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in mustard, celery seed, garlic, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Mash tomatoes.
Mix all remaining ingredients in large pot.
Bring to boil, then reduce to simmer.
This is best when simmered for a couple of hours.
Season with cajun-creole spices to taste (3 to 4 tablespoons for spicy).

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine pineapple and juice, water, sugar and salt.
Heat until sugar is dissolved; add jello.
Let stand until slightly congealed. Add celery, Dream Whip (prepared as directed on package).
Add cream cheese.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: ham (spam spread)
directions: Grate Spam and cheese.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.
Will keep for 1 week in refrigerator.

title: shipwreck kelly
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onions.
Put half of potatoes in greased casserole.
Place beans and juice and hamburg (broken up) next.
Add rest of potatoes and onions; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: emily's peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl at medium speed until well blended.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture.

title: cole slaw(great for summer)
directions: Slice green onions and their tops. Stir together green onion, corn, tomato, mayonnaise or salad dressing, yogurt, basil, salt and pepper in a large bowl. Cover and refrigerate
for 4 to 24 hours. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: party pups
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, onion, milk, salt, pepper and celery salt.
Add meat and green pepper; mix.
Divide into 12 equal parts.
Mold each portion in shape of frankfurter 1-inch thick. Wrap with bacon; secure with wooden pick.
Place on rack in broiler pan 5 inches from heat.
Broil for 8 minutes on one side. Turn and broil for 6 minutes or until bacon is lightly browned. Remove picks and serve.
Yields 12 servings.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk. At once, pour in unbaked pie shell.
Dash top with nutmeg.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes; 425° for 10 minutes longer.
Serve chilled.

title: chicken apricot
directions: Mix last three ingredients in a bowl. Place chicken pieces in a flat baking dish.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Use these proportions times the number of people to be served.
Serve with rice and salad.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple and mix with sugar, flour and eggs.
Melt margarine and pour over bread chunks (in another bowl).
In baking dish, put pineapple mix and then spread bread chunks over mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lazy daisy meatballs
directions: Mix meat, seasoning, cracker crumbs, water, and onion.
Form into 24 balls.
Roll in flour and brown in oil.
Mix soup and water and pour over meatballs.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Delicious served over rice.

title: green vegetable bake
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add cornstarch, salt, pepper and sour cream; mix well.
Stir in green vegetables.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese. Combine remaining 2 tablespoons butter and cracker crumbs.
Place on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great for leftovers.
Recipe for timid green vegetable eaters.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Add beaten egg yolks, either 3 or 4 with milk.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Remove from stove and stir in oleo.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made from 3 or 4 egg whites beaten until stiff with 1/4 cup sugar added gradually.
Bake in a 300° oven until brown.

title: tuna and pepper fricassee
directions: Preparation time: 10 minutes.
Cooking time: 20 minutes.

title: pia's italian country beans
directions: Heat oil and saute garlic until it becomes fragrant, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add green beans and saute 2 to 3 minutes until glossy and well coated.
Add broth and cook until beans are just tender-crisp.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and ham; serve. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and form into flattened ball.
Chill and cover with cocktail sauce.
Serve on crackers.

title: jo's banana cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions to make 2 layers. Slice each layer into 2 pieces horizontally to make 4 layers. Cook the Milnot, sugar and butter until thick.
Put sliced bananas between each layer, then pour hot icing over cake.
Yummy.
Can put whipped cream on top, if desired.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in topping; blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill 4 hours.
Put on fruit.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix jello in boiling water; set aside.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Beat milk until stiff; set aside. Crush crackers and add melted margarine; press in pan to make crust.
Mix all together and beat.
Pour in crust and let chill in refrigerator.

title: homemade ice cream("fast and easy")
directions: Strawberry or peach is great.
Put all in ice cream freezer and freeze with rock salt and ice.
Makes 6 quarts in about 45 minutes.

title: sausage and cornbread stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, cook sausage over medium heat until browned. Add cornbread stuffing, pecans and spices to sausage in skillet.
Stir until well mixed.
Add chicken broth slowly and evenly and mix until moist as you wish.
Stuff chicken or turkey. Great as a side dish, too.
Serves 8.

title: mary jane's coffee cake
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients at low speed until moist.
Beat at high speed until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix the last 3 ingredients together.
Alternate the cake batter with the filling mix, starting with batter and ending with small coating of filling mix.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: no bean dip
directions: Place the ingredients in crock-pot to heat.
Have fun dipping.

title: jack's special punch
directions: Make the lemonade.
Add to punch bowl.
Add rest of ingredients.
Can freeze some strawberries in an ice ring to float.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup water (boiling).
Add remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Put half of mixture in an 8 x 8-inch dish or mold.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
When set, spread with sour cream, then carefully pour on the remaining Jell-O mixture.
Place back in refrigerator until set.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour ingredients into buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash.
Pour off liquid and mash with back of a fork. Saute onion in butter.
Combine squash, onion, eggs, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs. Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 375°.
Use a small casserole or a small black spider pan.

title: grandma's tater tot casserole
directions: Press raw ground beef on bottom of glass baking dish.
Spread cream of mushroom soup on top of ground beef.
If using a vegetable, spread on top of soup.
Next, place cheese slices or Cheddar cheese across dish.
Layer rows of Tater Tots across cheese, covering the entire top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Serves approximately 8.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Peel onions.
Cut the unpared cucumbers and the onions into thin slices.
Layer and sprinkle with salt the onions and cucumbers in a ceramic or stainless steel bowl.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain.
Do not rinse.
Mix vinegar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed and sugar and stir into cucumbers.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package, omitting salt.
Mix remaining ingredients except for Cheez Whiz.
Pour in a baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: irish potato cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter together; add egg yolk.
Mix flour and baking powder and spices.
Alternate mashed potato and flour mixture and milk in with butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Last, fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in two 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: grandma's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, eggs, sugar, salt and spices in a large bowl. When well blended, add evaporated milk and continue mixing until mixed well. Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle pie with pumpkin pie spice. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350°. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool for 2 hours on cooling rack. Then serve with Cool Whip or refrigerate.

title: beef or pork stew
directions: Use the recipe for Beef or Pork Stew.
Put in a baking pan. Place 2 to 4 unbaked biscuits on the top.
Bake at 400° (hot oven) for 20 to 30 minutes, until browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone; break into pieces.
Heat soup and sour cream.
Grease bottom of baking dish.
Layer chicken in bottom.
Pour soup/sour cream mixture over top.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
May add poppy seed if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: german pancakes
directions: Blend flour, milk, eggs and salt in blender until smooth. Pour into flat 9 x 13-inch cake pan which has 6 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: easy chili
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Cook until beef is browned, stirring until it crumbles.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and remaining ingredients.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields about four cups.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Mix other ingredients and add Cool Whip last.

title: spankies
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, do not drain. Add spices. Lay slice cheese on top of mixture. After cheese melts mix thoroughly. Spread meat mixture on each slice of bread and put on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 400 degree oven until mixture starts to bubble. Remove from oven and enjoy!!!

title: garlic cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients, form into ball.
(I always put in serving bowl.)
Top with chopped walnuts.
Great with Triscuits.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix preserves, onion soup and dressing.
Place chicken in shallow pan, top with sauce.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour.

title: crivitz deluxe french dressing
directions: Put all together in a jar and put in the refrigerator.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and rinse potatoes, cut into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Use a wooden spoon handle to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Put potato in baking dish, sprinkle with herbs.

title: fruit bowl
directions: When the ingredients are mixed, add 3 tablespoons of Tang and 1 box instant vanilla pudding. Refrigerate overnight and serve.

title: biscotti regina(queen's cookies)
directions: Sift the flour, sugar and cinnamon into a large mixing bowl and cut in the lard until the mixture reaches the texture of a coarse meal.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and as much milk as necessary to hold the dough together.
Knead for a minute and then shape the dough into finger shaped pieces, about 1 1/2-inches long.
Roll each piece first in egg whites, then in the sesame seed so that is well covered with a layer of seeds.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake in a preheated 350° oven about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry-banana congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Fold in strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into 9 x 12-inch glass pan (a glass bowl or parfait glasses may also be used).
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over the top.
Gently pour remaining 1/2 of mixture over the sour cream layer. Refrigerate until congealed.
Garnish as desired.

title: mrs. edna wallace's famous "goulash"
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute peppers and onion until tender.
Then mix all ingredients except chili powder in a Dutch oven.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Then turn heat to simmer.
Simmer for 25 minutes.
Add chili powder and cook 5 minutes more.

title: forever wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a pint of sympathy.
Flavor with a bright fireside and loving kisses.
Bake well all of your life.

title: cucumber pickles(no-seal sweet)
directions: Dissolve salt in boiling water to cover cucumbers; pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours; drain.
Dissolve alum in boiling water; pour over cucumbers to cover.
Let stand 24 hours; drain. Cover cucumbers with boiling water; let stand 24 hours and drain. Bring spices and vinegar to a boil; pour over cucumbers and let stand 9 days.
Drain well; slice or cut cucumbers into chunks. Alternate sugar and cucumbers in jars.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: zucchini
directions: Let all ingredients simmer until tender.
Enjoy.

title: quick and easy canned peach cobbler
directions: Butter casserole dish and fill with peaches.
Stir in lemon juice and cinnamon.

title: lemon chicken breasts
directions: Place flour, salt and pepper in plastic storage bag.
Put chicken in bag, one piece at a time, and shake to coat.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Place chicken in frying pan and cook until light brown, turning occasionally.
Add lemon juice and mushrooms to frying pan.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 20 minutes. Serve over buttered noodles.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Layer vegetables in dish you are serving them in.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over.
Cover and chill for two hours.
Serve with slotted spoon.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; combine remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients, stirring until well mixed.
Spoon mixture into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.

title: lemon herb marinated chicken
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and let stand 30 minutes, turning once.
Broil 10 minutes, turning once.

title: raisin chews
directions: Rinse, drain and dry raisins.
Chop or grind chop walnuts. Beat eggs until foamy and gradually beat in sugar and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices into first mixture. Blend in raisins, nuts and orange rind.
Spread in well-greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes until lightly crusted on top.
Cut into squares while warm.
Cool; remove from pan.
Makes about 16 to 20 squares.

title: fresh rhubarb pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix sugar and flour. Turn 1/2 of the rhubarb into pastry-lined pie plate; sprinkle with half of the sugar mixture.
Repeat with remaining rhubarb and sugar mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust that has slits cut in it.
Seal and flute.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Cover edge with 2 to 3-inch strip of aluminum foil. Remove during last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hawaiian sausage casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Arrange pineapple, potatoes and sausage in 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
In small saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend in pineapple juice.
Cook until thick and bubbly. Remove from heat; stir in butter.
Pour over casserole.
Cover and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Dice chicken; add soups and all other ingredients, saving cheese for garnish.
Cook 30 minutes, covered, and 30 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.
Use a 9 x 13-inch or deep casserole dish.

title: manwich soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Season to taste; drain.
Set aside.
Cover potatoes, carrots, celery and onion with water; cook until tender. Remove from heat.
Add corn, beans, Manwich and ground beef. Return to heat and simmer for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until soft.
Add both cans of soup and Cheez Whiz.
Cook until cheese melts and blends.
Add rice and broccoli.
Turn into 2-quart casserole dish and bake uncovered at 350° for 3 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken breasts until tender.
Save chicken broth. Cool chicken and cut into large pieces.
Mix stuffing in melted butter.
Put 1/2 of the stuffing into a large baking dish.
Add chicken and chicken soup.
Mix with 1 cup of broth and 1 cup of water.
Pour over mixture and add remainder of crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot.

title: sloppy joses
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender.
Stir to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Add soup, chili powder and seasonings.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Serve on rolls.
Top with cheese.

title: carol's barbecue sauce sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Put cherries and lemon-lime soda in ice cube trays and freeze. Spoon 3 pints of sherbet into punch bowl.
Let soften at room temperature about 5 minutes.
Slowly pour in lemon-lime soda, stirring slightly.
Float generous scoopfuls of remaining sherbet on top of punch.
Add maraschino cherry ice cubes to punch.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut tops off the potatoes lengthwise and scoop out potato. Mash potato with the sour cream, onion salt and chives.
Fill skins with potato mixture. Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: salad supreme spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti; rinse.
Combine all ingredients. Chill for 24 hours to combine all flavors.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Sift together and add flour, soda and salt.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Remove from oven and pour hot glaze over cake in pan.
Let stand in pan 2 hours.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil over high fire about 14 minutes or until peanuts smell done and the mixture is a cream color.
Remove from fire.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons of soda.
Pour onto two buttered cookie sheets. Spread thin and let cool.
Break into desired size pieces.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Heat oil and butter in a skillet; add onion and mushrooms. Saute at low heat.
Add meat and cook about 10 minutes; add bouillon and continue cooking.
Mix flour and seasoning with sour cream and cream of mushroom soup.
Add to first mixture.
Cook slowly until thick, but do not boil.
Serve with noodles.
Will serve 6 people.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Cut in bacon drippings. Add milk slowly.
Mix well.
On floured counter, roll out to about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut and bake in preheated oven at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: italian corn
directions: Do not drain corn.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir a lot while baking.
May add 1/2 chopped onion.

title: strawberry refrigerator cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers finely and place more than half of them in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cream butter well and mix with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Spread this mixture over crumbs and then cover with strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with the remaining vanilla wafer crumbs. Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: old fashioned sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Cream wet ingredients together.
Mix both mixtures together.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: best ever breadsticks
directions: In saucepan, heat milk, sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine milk mixture, yeast and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to form stiff dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Punch dough down.
Pinch off golf ball size pieces.
Roll into pencil-size strips.
Place on greased baking sheet 1-inch apart. Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Combine egg white and water; brush over sticks.
Sprinkle with salt or cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yield:
about 18 breadsticks.

title: sausage and cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Roll out each biscuit into 5-inch circle. Place each in an ungreased muffin cup. Cut sausage in fifths and brown in skillet; drain. Divide sausage among cups. In a small bowl, combine eggs, cheese and scallions. Spoon about 2 full tablespoons into each cup. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes (until browned).

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter.
Add the sugar and continue creaming, while adding the combined syrups.
Blend all.
Then beat in eggs with the pecans, salt, and vanilla.
Turn into partially baked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until no filling adheres to the tip of the knife.

title: no-bake fruit cake
directions: Put the milk, marshmallows and orange juice into a large bowl; let stand until needed.
Roll graham crackers into fine crumbs. In a large bowl, mix the crumbs, spices, raisins, dates and nuts. Add the candied fruits. Add the milk mixture.
Mix with a spoon, then with hands until crumbs are moistened. Press firmly into a 9-inch tube pan or loaf pan with waxed paper lining.
Top with additional fruit and nuts.
Cover tightly. Chill 2 days before slicing.
Keep in cool place.
Makes 3 1/2 pounds.

title: flaxseed bread
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons water and set aside until bubbly, about 5 minutes. Mix in honey, oil, salt and the remaining water. Add flaxseed meal, whole-wheat flour and 1 cup of the bread flour. Mix well. Stir in enough of the remaining bread flour to make a soft and kneadable dough. Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured board and knead for 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic. Coat a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick spray. Shape the dough into a loaf and place in the pan. Cover. Let rise in a warm place until double in bulk, about 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until loaf is browned on top and sounds hollow when tapped. Cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes, together.
Pour mixture into large casserole dish.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Crush corn flakes and pour on top of casserole. Cook 15 more minutes.

title: fat man french toast
directions: Beat eggs and milk together. Mix cinnamon and sugar according to taste and add to egg mixture. Dip bread into mixture until heavily coated. Fry in butter until browned to perfection. In another small pan, combine 1/2 stick of butter and a bunch of maple syrup; heat. Place French Toast on a plate and on each slice, load it up with cream cheese and spread it thick. Stack 3 or 4 slices high with cream cheese between each slice. Completely cover and drown this with your favorite buttery syrup mix. Garnish with pecans.

title: green chile macaroni
directions: Place all ingredients in a buttered casserole, except 1/2 cheese.
Cover with milk.
Add 1/2 cup cheese to top last.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Melt together 1/2 stick of margarine and cheese.
Mix with broccoli.
Melt other 1/2 stick of margarine and mix with the Ritz crackers (after they have been crushed).
Top broccoli mixture with Ritz cracker mixture (sprinkled) on top of broccoli mixture and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Drain fruit; save juice.
To 2/3 cup juice add dry pudding and mix.
Add fruit to pudding mixture.
Put in refrigerator 8 hours or overnight.
Just before serving, add sliced bananas if desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and oil.
Blend well.
Add zucchini and dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Grease and flour bread pan.
Bake at 350° for metal or 325° for glass pan for 50 to 60 minutes.
Fill pan 1/2 full.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: layered salad
directions: Fill bowl 1/3 full of lettuce.
Layer remaining ingredients. Cover and chill overnight.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Add the first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Add dressing to taste.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm with Melba rounds or plain crackers.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Saute zucchini, onion and garlic in oil until lightly browned. Season with salt and pepper.
Place in pie shell.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Combine eggs with cream and pour on top of zucchini mixture.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan and parsley.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool slightly and serve.

title: lana's peanut butter cream pie
directions: Soften cream cheese then mix with mixer until fluffy. Next, add confectioners sugar and peanut butter. Mix well. Gradually add milk and mix. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust. Refrigerate until set.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Dump peanut butter, dates and butter together. Add the confectioners sugar, a little bit at a time.
Refrigerate a little while.
Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate in microwave. Roll balls in chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: fresh tomato-basil spaghettine
directions: Blanch spaghettine; drain.
Set aside.
Heat saute pan over medium-high heat.
Add oil and garlic; saute garlic about 1 minute; do not brown.

title: czechoslavakian cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and egg yolks.
Add flour, mix and add nuts. Grease 8-inch square pan.
Spread 1/2 dough and add preserves. Cover with remaining dough.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: next best thing to robert redford(prepare the day before or early on day you want it.)
directions: Prepare crust until crumb-like.
Press into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Add all ingredients in a large pot.
Cover with water and cook, covered, for 1 hour.
Remove lid and boil down sauce slightly, if desired.
Serve over rice.

title: baptist chocolate pudding cake
directions: Frost while hot.
Melt margarine, milk, cocoa and vanilla. Add powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Add nuts on top.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Separate biscuits and roll out flat.
Half apples, peel and core.
Cover apples with biscuits; place flat side down in baking dish.
Combine
remaining ingredients and heat to boil. Pour over apples.
Cover
with
foil	and
bake at 350° for 45 minutes, basting every 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: zucchini casserole with sour cream
directions: Peel and grate the zucchini. Saute the zucchini and onions together in 2 tablespoons oleo for 10 minutes. Combine in a bowl the carrots, sour cream and soup.
In another bowl, add the stuffing. Pour 1/2 cup melted oleo on the stuffing.
Mix in the package of herb mix and set aside.
Drain zucchini.
Fold in soup and sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle layer of the stuffing on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Add the zucchini mixture.
Add the remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown.

title: chicken chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, boil chicken 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Bone and cube.
In Dutch oven, heat oil on medium. Saute onion, green pepper and garlic until tender.
Add chicken, tomatoes, beans, picante sauce and seasonings; bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer for 20 minutes.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Top with cheese, avocado and sour cream, if desired.

title: chicken with cheese sauce
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Bake chicken breasts for 20 minutes.
In saucepan combine heavy cream and cheese soup.
Simmer and stir over medium heat until smooth.
Add chicken breasts and serve.

title: portuguese chicken saute
directions: Rub salt and pepper into chicken.
Heat oil and butter in a frying pan or stove top casserole.
Cook chicken about 15 minutes over medium-low heat until it is brown all over; remove from pan.

title: steak soup
directions: Place all ingredients except butter and flour in slow cooker. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
One hour before serving, turn to high setting.
Make a roux of melted butter and flour. Pour into soup and stir until thickened.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Remove seeds from fresh pumpkin.
Clean of all pulp and lay onto on jellyroll pan.
Sprinkle well with water.
Salt to taste and bake at 250 degrees for about an hour.
Watch to see that they do not get too dry.
Mix sugar, salt, cumin, cinnamon, ginger, and pepper in a bowl.
Add pumpkin seeds and toss.
Cool and enjoy.

title: potluck picnic mold
directions: Microwave water on High for 2 minutes or until boiling. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in mayonnaise, cold water and vinegar.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat to fluffy. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8.
Each serving contains 55 calories, 0 milligrams cholesterol and 70 milligrams sodium.

title: iceland potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and boil until done.
Melt butter in a frying pan on low heat.
Add sugar to melted butter and bring to a boil.
The mixture will be the consistency of a syrup.
Do not overheat! Drain the potatoes and let them simmer a few minutes.
Pour potatoes and syrup in a serving dish.

title: beef goulash vegetable soup
directions: Saute beef, onions and celery until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Add cans of vegetables, tomato sauce, beef bouillon and seasoning.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add noodles and simmer until noodles are tender.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet; add rice and stir until coated.
Add onion and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth, water, thyme, salt and pepper; stir.
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes until rice is tender.
Snip parsley and sprinkle over top.

title: shrimp & crab casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350 until bubbly in center.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken breasts, then cut into medium pieces.
Cook onion (chopped) with butter for a few minutes.
Add these to cream of chicken soup, green chilies and 1/2 cup sour cream.
Mix well. Put on shells and roll.
Top with 1 cup sour cream and cream of celery soup (mixed well), then top with cheese.
Cook at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and form into a ball in a dish.
Mix the last 2 ingredients and pour over ball.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: fire burgers
directions: Mix ground meat, diced onions and diced potatoes together in mixing bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Then take hands and make into large patties.
Put into foil and wrap tight.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Good to put on grill.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Fill pie shell with strawberries.
Mix other 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Boil until starts to thicken, stirring constantly. Cool slightly.
Pour over berries. Chill until set. Top with Cool Whip.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine until soft in mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar, creaming after each addition until well blended.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to cream mixture.
Blend and chill dough.
Roll out dough, small amount at a time, to 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured board. Cut out.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes (no longer).
Frost with Valentine Cookie Frosting year 'round.

title: frozen salad
directions: Blend first four ingredients together.
Fold in cherries. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch square pan and freeze.
Let sit for 10 minutes before cutting into squares and serving.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Bake in an electric frypan.
Line skillet with waxed paper. Melt margarine in skillet at 200°.
Turn selector off.
Spread brown sugar, then spread with crushed pineapple.
Prepare cake mix, adding 2 eggs and 1/3 cup of pineapple juice.
Pour cake batter into frypan.
Turn heat selector to 270°.
Cover with frypan lid, open vent.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spiced red cabbage(no dairy, low-fat)
directions: In a saucepan, combine shredded cabbage with all ingredients except apples and sugar.
Cover and cook over moderate heat for 15 minutes, tossing several times so the cabbage will cook evenly. Add apples and toss again.
Cover and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add sugar.
If more water is needed during cooking, add 2 or 3 tablespoons.
When ingredients are done cooking, all moisture should have cooked away.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Rinse and drain.
Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Mix well and let simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Mix cottage cheese and sour cream together in bowl.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Mix oil and egg to milk; mix with a fork.
Make a well in center of flour mixture and add oil mixture.
Stir with a fork.
Batter will be lumpy.
Add blueberries and stir easy.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: butterscotch coffee spice bars
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl, combine shortening and brown sugar and beat until creamy.
Add egg and beat well.
Combine water and coffee and add butterscotch chips and nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: spicy texas chili
directions: Place beans in a large saucepan.
Cover with cold water. Bring the water to a boil over high heat.
Skim off any foam; reduce heat to moderately low to maintain beans at simmer.

title: nut and date bars
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl. Mix by hand with a spoon. Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch brownie pan and bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes. Remove from oven and dust with powdered sugar. Cut in squares while warm.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of warm water.
Mix together 5 cups of water, oil, sugar and salt.
Add flour and stir until well mixed.
Put dough on floured board.
Knead until smooth and does not stick to hands.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Let set 10 minutes.
Make into loaves.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 loaves.

title: tortelli appetizers
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Chill and cut in 1-inch strips and serve.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: In small bowl, combine 1/3 cup catsup and water; stir in bread crumbs and set aside.
In large bowl, combine meat, eggs, onion, salt and pepper; add bread crumb mixture and mix thoroughly.
Shape into loaf 8 x 4 x 1 1/2-inches in shallow pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Combine 1/4 cup catsup and syrup and spread over top of meat loaf.
Bake additional 10 minutes.
Serve 5 minutes after removing from oven.

title: guilt-free blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together and divide into 12 nonstick muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings, 3 muffins each. Each contains 1 milk, 1 egg, 1 bread, 1 fruit and 3 extras.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended well.
Put into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the eggs, sugar and margarine.
Mix in applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients and mix 1 cup of flour mixture with nuts and raisins.
Fold in dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nut mixture last.
Bake in floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: blueberry loaf
directions: Beat cheese, oil and eggs well.
Add cake mix and mix well. Fold in blueberries.
Bake in a loaf pan at 325° until done (45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread refried beans in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer with hamburger, onion and cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with lettuce and tomato.
Dip with chips.

title: hot meat filling
directions: Mix all together and bake in 350° oven for an hour.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Halve baked potatoes lengthwise; scoop out each potato, leaving 1/4-inch of potato on the skins.
Brush skins with oil. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place on tinfoil lined baking sheet.
Bake in 475° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, turning over occasionally until crisp and browned around the edges.
Top as desired.

title: french apple pie
directions: In a saucepan, cook apples just until tender in a small amount of water.
When apples are cooked, add raisins, butter, lemon juice and spices.
Mix cornstarch with sugar and stir in.
Let mix cool slightly.
Pour into pie shell and cover with top crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 325° or until lightly browned.
Let pie cool and cover the top crust with a glaze made with powdered sugar, 1 tablespoon butter, 1 teaspoon lemon juice and small amount milk.
This should be thin.
Spoon over the top crust and chill before serving.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt shortening.
Add sugar and mix.
Add egg and vanilla. Add dry ingredients in small amounts and mix.
Put in well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips over top.
Put in 350° oven.
Take out after 3 minutes and run knife through chips to get marble effect, then return to oven and continue baking 25 minutes.

title: blueberry angel dessert
directions: In a large bowl beat cream cheese and sugar, fold into whipped topping and cake cubes. Spread evenly into ungreased 9x13 pan. Top with filling. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before cutting.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: mother's cherry salad
directions: Combine flour, butter and nuts in a small bowl.
Mix with hands and press dough evenly into a 13 inch by 9 inch baking dish. Bake at 300 degrees for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: creamy spam and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a 2-quart casserole with vegetable spray.
Cook macaroni according to directions; drain.
In casserole, combine macaroni, broccoli, Spam and red pepper.
In small saucepan, stir together milk, flour and pepper until flour is dissolved.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until thickened. Reduce heat to low.
Add cheese; stir until melted.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter together.
Mix brown and white sugar and add to shortening gradually, creaming until light and fluffy.
Combine egg and milk and add to mixture.
Fold in rolled oats.
Add sifted dry ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: yellow scratch cake
directions: Mix. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Boil squash and sugar for 20 minutes.
Add pineapple and lemon juice and boil for 5 more minutes.
Add jello.
Pour in hot ingredients, stirring constantly, while mixing good.
Then remove from heat.
Pour into sterile jelly jars; seal and refrigerate.

title: sweet broiled grapefruit
directions: Cut membrane out of the center of each grapefruit half.
Cut around each section so it will be easy to spoon out when eating. Place 1 tablespoon butter in the center of each half.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over each.
Broil until butter is melted and sugar is bubbly.
Garnish with a cherry, if desired. Serve immediately.
Yields 2 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Bake potatoes in oven and cool.
Mix mayonnaise, Miracle Whip and mustard together.
Next, mix dill pickle juice, pickles, onion, eggs and cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Quarter potatoes and add to mixture.
Mix well and refrigerate until served.

title: chicken and pepper stir-fry
directions: In a hot wok, add olive oil and chicken.
Cook 2 minutes or until half done.
Add sliced peppers, onion and mushrooms.
Once peppers have softened, push chicken and peppers onto side of wok and spread broccoli and cauliflower around the edge.
Add a tablespoon of water to the middle of the wok.
Place top on wok and allow to steam to soften and cook remaining vegetables.
Serve with brown rice or angel hair pasta.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in water until they are done, about 45 minutes. Peel and cut them into pieces, then mix all the ingredients in a bowl and eat warm.
Put in refrigerator to eat cold if you like too.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix refried beans and taco seasoning together.
Spread mixture into bottom of round glass tray.
Spread layer of avocado dip, then layer of sour cream.
Top with cheese, tomatoes, black olives and green onions.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: lemon sauce
directions: In a heavy saucepan, add the first 3 ingredients.
Blend thoroughly, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place on medium heat until mixture reaches the boiling point and thickens.
Add as much of the juice from one lemon as necessary to get the desired taste.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: bible honey cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Make a well and add next 3 ingredients.
Beat all together until smooth and add 2 whole Jeremiah 17:11.
Beat for 5 minutes by hand, then add 2 cups 1 Samuel 30:12.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix the sugar and margarine, salt, eggs, and vinegar.
Add the coconut, pecans, and raisins.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300°- 325° for 35-40 minutes.

title: george's hash
directions: Put through food processor or food grinder, so it looks chopped. Fry slowly in a little oil until all is tender.
If you have leftover gravy, can serve that over hash.

title: prize-winning baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in Crisco.
Gradually add milk and make into soft dough.
Roll out on floured board 1/2-inch thick.
Cut, using a 2 1/2-inch cutter (a drinking glass dipped in flour works well).
Put on oiled square baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: frank's pickled peppers
directions: Pack peppers into a quart jar or storage container.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a hard boil. Remove from heat and cool for 30 minutes.
Pour liquid over peppers.
Cover jar.
Refrigerate 3 days before serving.
Makes 1 quart.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground chuck, bread crumbs, onion, milk, eggs and next 4 seasonings.
Gently shape into 1-inch balls.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Brown meatballs; drain excess grease.
Heat chili sauce and grape jelly until jelly is melted.
Add in meatballs.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients, one at a time, in large bowl.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit bowl
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges; do not use juice.
Mix the apple mix, oranges, strawberries and pineapple.
Refrigerate overnight. When ready to serve, add the bananas and peaches.

title: easter egg special (candy)
directions: Knead well, and shape into large or small eggs. Set aside to ripen for a few days. Either dip eggs into melted sweet chocolate or dribble hot chocolate over them. When chocolate hardens, decorate eggs with white icing and or flowers.

title: broccoli casserole with chicken
directions: Combine broccoli, chicken, mushroom soup, milk, black pepper, Cheddar cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions in mixing bowl. Place in
1 1/2-quart size baking dish. Bake for 30 minutes. Sprinkle remaining onions over top and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: fresh mozzarella and pesto tart
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Cut chicken in bite size pieces.
On a lightly floured surface, roll bread dough into a 10-inch circle. Place in a greased 11-inch tart pan with a removable bottom, pressing to fit into pan.
Prick crust with fork.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Transfer to a wire rack, leaving oven on.

Meanwhile, in a large skillet, heat oil, stir-fry chicken, onion, pepper and lemon pepper seasoning over medium heat for 5 to 6 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and vegetables are crisp and tender. Spread pesto atop the crust.
Top with chicken mixture, tomatoes and fresh Mozzarella.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.
Remove from pan; place on a serving platter.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 6.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels.
Cook and stir hamburger and onion in a 10-inch skillet until hamburger is light brown; drain.
Stir in bacon and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until rice is tender, about 30 minutes.
(Add small amount of water during cooking, if necessary.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: lindy's cheesecake
directions: Butter 10-inch spring-form pan.
Combine flour, sugar, lemon rind and vanilla.
Make well in center and add egg yolk and butter.
Work mixture with hands until well blended.
Cover and chill for about 1 hour.
Roll dough about 1/4-inch thick or less on floured surface.
Place in bottom of spring-form pan.
Line sides with remaining dough which has been rolled and cut to fit. (I have trouble rolling out the dough, so I pat the crust out in the pan instead.)

title: orange kiss-me cake
directions: Squeeze orange and save the juice.
Grind pulp and rind of orange with raisins and walnuts.
Mix flour, soda, sugar and salt. Add shortening and 1/3 cup milk.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes.
Fold in orange mixture.
Bake in greased and floured 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° about 40 to 50 minutes.
Drip 1/3 cup orange juice over warm cake.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: zucchini bake
directions: In 2-quart shallow baking dish, combine all ingredients except stuffing mix and butter.
Toss stuffing mix with butter and spoon over vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 cups.

title: sweet sour meatballs
directions: Form hamburger into meatballs.
Heat chili sauce and cranberry sauce together.
Put meatballs in and cook over low heat 1 hour.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Peel and chunk the zucchini.
Mix with the lime and water. Let stand 24 hours.
Stir twice a day. Drain and rinse in cold water. Let stand in cold water 12 hours.
Heat the vinegar, sugar, pickling spice and coloring.
Let stand 12 hours.
Cook 35 minutes.
Put into hot pint jars and seal.

title: pecan delights(you can freeze dough for make-ahead treats.)
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar, water and vanilla. Separately combine nuts and flour. Slowly and thoroughly add nut/flour mixture to butter mixture. Form into logs. Put on cookie sheet in freezer until solid.
Put frozen cookies into airtight bag and store in freezer until ready to bake.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a mixing bowl, add flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Blend together.
Then add egg, shortening and milk.
Mix well.
Coat 1-quart baking dish with butter.
Add peaches.
Drain syrup off of 1 can.
Place 6 1/8 inch squares of butter over peaches, evenly spaced.
Sprinkle cinnamon evenly over peaches.
Then spoon pastry dough over peaches.
Bake on 400° for 30 minutes.

title: ants on a log
directions: Fill celery sticks with peanut butter or cream cheese. Sprinkle with chocolate flavored sprinkles.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Rub a large gratin dish with garlic (earthenware will take the garlic better) or put the peeled cloves through a garlic press, rubbing the pure and juices all over the sides and bottom of the dish and discarding any solid debris that remains.
Let it sit for a few minutes until the garlic has dried and is no longer tacky to the touch.
Butter the dish liberally and pack the potatoes in lightly salted layers.
Barely cover the potatoes in milk and bring to a simmer on the top of the stove (if using an earthenware dish, protect it with an asbestos pad underneath).
Dribble a thin layer of cream over the surface.
Dot with thin shavings of butter and bake at 375° to 400° for about 45 to 50 minutes until the liquid has been absorbed.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: garden potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Boil potatoes with skins for about 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool.
Dice potatoes with skins into bite size pieces.
Spoon potatoes into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Moisten potatoes.
Combine peppers, onion, parsley, Canadian bacon and cheese.
Spread pepper mixture over top of potatoes.
Drizzle with margarine.
Season with salt and pepper. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Low-fat recipe. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: grace's meat rolls
directions: Separate slices of meat and spread out flat.
Thinly spread each slice with the cream cheese mixture.
Roll up and place in a covered container.
Chill.
Cut each roll into three pieces.
May be frozen if you wish to make several days before serving.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: quickie yeast biscuits
directions: Combine butter, sugar and egg in large bowl.
Beat well.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Gradually add flour.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
I store and use as needed for a week or so.

title: fruit stack dippers
directions: Alternate 3 pieces of any combination of fruit and cheese on plastic or wooden picks.
Serve with Lime Yogurt Dip.
Makes about 40 appetizers.

title: strawberry spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach well.
Tear spinach into bite size pieces. Slice strawberries.
Stir into spinach.
Blend dressing ingredients and pour over spinach-strawberry mix.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Chop up and spread chicken in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cover with stuffing and pour broth on until moist. Bake at 350° for 1
hour or until brown and bubbly.

title: meringue
directions: Beat until stiff the egg whites and salt.
Add sugar and beat. Cook water and cornstarch until clear.
Add to egg whites and beat until well mixed.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix ingredients, tossing lightly with sour cream.
Chill overnight.
Serve on lettuce cups.

title: black russian cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, pudding, eggs, coffee and kahlua and creme de cocoa in a large mixing bowl.
Beat about 4 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon into a well-greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove cake from pan when cool. Punch holes in cake with meat fork and spoon topping over.

title: easy strawberry cake
directions: Place one bag mini marshmallows in bottom of greased pan. Sprinkle cake mix over marshmallows.
Sprinkle jello over cake mix.
Spoon partially thawed strawberries evenly over this.
Then sprinkle 1/2 to 1/3 cup water over all.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let set 30 minutes before serving.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Brown bacon bits in skillet.
Remove bacon and saute onion in fat until yellow.
Add flour, sugar and vinegar.
Add enough of the liquid from the beans to make a medium-thin sauce.
Add beans which have been heated and drained; stir lightly.
Bacon may be mixed in lightly or sprinkle over top.
Frozen beans may be used in this recipe as well as fresh green beans cooked homestyle which are "left over" from a previous meal.

title: reduced fat cake
directions: Use pan size as directed on cake mix.
Spray with nonstick spray.
In a medium bowl, beat together cake mix, water, egg whites and applesauce until smooth.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake according to package directions.
Garnish with fresh berries.

title: old fashioned potato candy
directions: Boil potato until tender, mash until there are no lumps.
Add vanilla.
Mix in confectioners sugar until the mixture can be rolled 1/4 inch thick.
Spread dough with smooth peanut butter. Roll, chill and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Crumble raw (do not brown) lean meat into water.
Add all ingredients, bring to boil, then simmer for 3 hours.
Remove garlic toes and bay leaves.
Add whole red peppers if desired for spicier taste.
Can be used also over spaghetti, serve with shredded cheese over either dish.

title: mrs. martin's pineapple dream dessert
directions: Tear up angel food cake in pieces into glass pan (9 x 13-inch).
Make pudding according to directions.
Drain pineapple. Mix pineapple and pudding.
Pour over cake.
Cover with whipped cream.

title: coconut pies
directions: Beat eggs with the cut margarine.
Put in sugar, milk and coconut.
Bake at 350° in unbaked shells for 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: slush
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale together.
Put in plastic
container	to
freeze.
Stir
each hour until frozen. Remove
from freezer 1/2 hour before serving and break up with a fork.
Fill serving glasses with partially thawed slush and a little ginger ale.	Stir and serve before it thaws.

title: sweet rolls
directions: In large bowl dissolve yeast in warm water.
Measure flour by "dip-level-pour" method or by sifting in a separate bowl.
Mix milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and half the flour to the yeast.
Mix with spoon until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to handle easy.
Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth. Round up in greased bowl, bring greased side up.
Cover with cloth. Let rise in warm place, until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; let rise again until almost double, about 30 minutes.
Shape, let rise and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Mix all together; add salt and pepper to taste.

title: lemon sponge cake
directions: Slice angel food cake with knife into thin slices.
Mix lemon pie filling and lemon yogurt together.
Layer slices of cake and mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients. Add rest of ingredients. Just stir to mix. Do not beat. Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pina colada(alcoholic drink)
directions: Mix pineapple juice, cream of coconut and rum.
Blend in fine ice.
Pour into large glass.
Garnish with pineapple slices. Insert straw for your drinking pleasure.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and spices.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 6 corn tortillas.
Pour meat mixture over tortillas.
Add 6 more tortillas.
Pour soup over all and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn pie
directions: Mix crumbs and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Set aside 1/2 cup and press remainder into 9-inch pie pan to form shell.

title: corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
In large bowl, mix flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix milk, butter and egg in 2nd bowl.
Add slowly to dry ingredients just until combined.
Stir in corn gently.
Spoon into muffin tins. Bake approximately 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: With electric mixer, blend oil, egg and milk.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together and add to milk mixture. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and beat one more minute.
Melt butter in a 10-inch heavy iron skillet.
Then add brown sugar; sprinkle evenly over melted butter.
Arrange pineapple slices on top of sugar mixture.
Decorate with pecans and cherries if desired.
Carefully pour batter over the fruit. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Immediately turn upside down on serving plate.
Leave skillet over cake several minutes, then remove.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut lard into flour and salt with fork or pastry blender until pea size particles.
Mix egg, vinegar and water with fork.
Add to flour.
Blend and roll into crusts.
Bake at 375° to 400°.
Enough for 4 pie shells.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown the meat and add chili along with Ragu and allow to simmer.
In a small frying pan, saute tortillas in a small amount of oil.
Keep tortillas warm in a dish towel.
Spoon chili mix and sprinkle cheese in each tortilla and roll.
Place them in a baking dish and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon in a bowl.
Combine eggs, oil and vanilla in a small bowl; mix well.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well.
Fold in zucchini and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake for one hour.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: honey-oatmeal muffins(nonfat)
directions: Add milk, applesauce, egg and honey to combined remaining ingredients, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened. Fill 12 greased or paper-lined size muffin cups.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple pie in a poke
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Coat apples well and place in pie shell.
Combine last 3 ingredients.
Dab topping on apples. Put pie into large brown paper bag.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°. Bag will not burn.

title: my favorite butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a pot, melt butter and brown sugar. Add to granulated sugar and vanilla extract.
Mix well.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate morsels (chips) and chopped nuts.

title: quick scampi
directions: In a nonstick skillet, saute 1 tablespoon olive oil and chopped garlic.
Add seafood and gently saute for 5 to 7 minutes. Serve over rice.
Add chopped fresh scallions.

title: mock date pudding
directions: Mix together in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This cake may be cooled, then cut in cubes and layered in a bowl with whipped cream and bananas.

title: smoothie fruitee dip
directions: Combine pudding mix and sour cream in a bowl; beat well. Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: pineapple carrot bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and soda. Combine both mixtures. Add remaining ingredients. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dinner-in-a-dish
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Put in casserole dish a layer of browned meat, a layer of potatoes and a layer of sliced onions. continue with layers of meat, potatoes and onions.
Dilute can of soup with milk; pour over casserole and bake in oven at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours until potatoes are done.

title: escalloped corn and oyster casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine.
Place in a greased casserole.
Place dots of margarine on top.
Bake in 350° oven, 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until custard in center sets up.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan the pineapple.
Sprinkle over the pineapple the coconut.
Dump and smooth over mixture the yellow cake mix.
Dot entire surface with butter.
Do not mix. Bake at 350°
for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: savory pork chops
directions: Place chops in skillet and brown.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place onion slices on top of chops.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread beans in 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with beef, taco sauce, then cheese. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until bubbly. Top with olives and sour cream. Use nachos, tostados or Doritos to dip with.

title: brandied chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter and steak sauce.
Mix remaining ingredients (except fruits).
Pour over chicken; simmer 30 minutes.
Arrange in greased casserole with fruits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until well browned and glazed.
Serves 4.

title: apple brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Add the flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Mix well, then add apples and nuts.
Spread in well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, sprinkle with cinnamon and bake for 25 minutes.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Melt 2 minutes.
Place crackers on foil on cookie sheet.
Pour syrup over all; sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: rainbow soup
directions: Chicken or neckbone can be used.
Stir in carrots, peas, corn, green beans, tomato sauce, onion and potatoes.
Pour nearly all juice off vegetables.
Store in container for later use and refrigerate.
Pour all ingredients into broth.
(Add celery, if desired.)
Cook until diced potatoes are done, approximately 1 hour.
Serve piping hot with your favorite cornbread or hot rolls.

title: italian sausage casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown sausage; drain grease.
In greased baking dish, combine sausage, spaghetti sauce, mostaccioli, onion and Parmesan cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into two portions.
Mix flour and salt; pound into meat; set aside remaining flour.
Brown meat in small amount of hot shortening.
Place meat in small shallow baking dish.
Blend remaining flour with drippings in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese, and cook, stirring constantly, till mixture boils.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake in moderate oven (350 degrees) 2 hours or till meat and vegetables are tender. Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Return to oven for few minutes.
Makes two servings.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Mix together rice, soup, oil, milk and French dressing.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture in a large casserole dish (greased).
Put chicken breasts on top of this mixture.
Then pour the rest of mixture over the chicken.
Top with lots of grated Parmesan cheese and sliced slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
(If it starts to brown too much, put foil on top.)

title: clams or mussels sauteed(vongole or cozze saltati)
directions: Scrub and rinse
shells of fresh clams.
Place clams in large skillet.
Add all ingredients to the clams and cook over medium high heat,
shaking
pan
and tossing occasionally.
As soon as clams open,
they
are
done.
Discard any that do not open. Serve immediately
with
crusty
Italian
bread, if desired. Makes 4
servings.
You
can
also combine mussels and clams together.

title: "frankie's" chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Combine all ingredients in a large pot and simmer for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Stir occasionally.
Makes about 6 quarts.
Freezes well.

title: asparagus au gratin
directions: Steam asparagus until tender.
Melt butter and stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk until mixture thickens.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip, pineapple and pecans.
Pour into crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Put the oleo, Crisco, cocoa and 1 cup water in a saucepan. Bring to a boil; pour over mixture of white sugar and flour.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased sheath cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla to dry mixture. Blend with mixer for about 3 minutes on medium.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: zippy cranberry cooler
directions: Combine cranberry juice with lemonade and water.
Before serving add ice cubes and soda.

title: beefy sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Shape into small balls. Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine with hands sausage, grated cheese and Bisquick.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: crystal's baked beans(old fashioned taste with a quick prepared head start.)
directions: Heat frypan.
Fry bacon and onion together until crisp.
Drain. Add both beans to an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Fold in all the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
If having a large group over, double the recipe and use a 9 x 13-inch size pan.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Mmm mmm good!

title: peaches and cream cheese cake
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 9-inch deep dish pan.
Beat the first 7 ingredients and pour into prepared pan.
Drain off all juice from peaches and place fruit on top of batter.
Reserve juice.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and juice.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon on top of peaches 1-inch from the edge. Sprinkle over cream cheese filling the sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is golden brown. Refrigerate.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix in large bowl, the first 6 ingredients.
Mix water, 4 tablespoons cocoa and 1 cup margarine in saucepan; bring to a boil. Add cocoa mixture to other mixture and beat well.
Pour into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Remove from pan and cool.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix all first 3 ingredients with fork and press in bottom of baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix by hand (last 5 ingredients).
Mix well and pour over baked crust.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until light brown.
Yield:
100 servings.

title: angel wings "funkie pastry"
directions: Combine egg yolks and milk.
Add flour until stiff enough to roll.
Roll dough thin; cut into diamond shapes.
Make dash in middle; put one end through to make wings.
Fry in oil in deep frypan when hot.
Put in a few wings until lightly golden, about 1 minute.
Turn over; put on brown paper sack.
When cool and ready to eat, sprinkle or sift with powdered sugar.

title: brighten-up breakfast(method:  skillet)
directions: In a medium size bowl, beat together the eggs and milk; set aside.
Slice bacon into small pieces; fry in large skillet. Drain away most of the grease into a heat-resistant can.
Add cubed potatoes and heat them through (about 3 to 5 minutes).
Add eggs; cook until done.
Top with cheese and serve.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: In casserole, place pork chops. On each chop, put 1 slice lemon or orange, 1 tablespoon chopped onion, 1 tablespoon dark brown sugar and 3 tablespoons catsup. Cover with foil. Put in 375° oven for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes. Meat will be tender and thin sauce is delicious.

title: stuffing hot dish
directions: Place stuffing mix on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Add cooked rice over top of stuffing.
Next, layer cream of mushroom soup and sour cream, mixed together.
Then add layer of sliced mushrooms.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, celery and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza with a hamburger crust
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, salt and oregano with a spoon in a large bowl.
Stir in *1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Spread meat mix in ungreased 10-inch pizza pan or on the bottom and side of 10-inch pie pan.
Pour *1/2 cup tomato sauce on top of meat mixture. Spread kidney beans on top of tomato sauce.
Cut cheese into strips and arrange in crisscross design on beans.
Bake uncovered at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate
the
raw
sweet potatoes and add to milk, sugar, eggs, butter
and spices.
Bake in a well-greased baking dish in a
325° oven
for 1 hour or until brown on top and firm in the center. This will serve about 8.
