It can be used with the main meal or as a dessert with a sauce or whipped cream.

title: pizza rounds
directions: Brown sausage and ground chuck.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients and cook until cheese melts.
Spread on party bread and broil on cookie sheet until bubbly and toasted.

title: vegetable rice salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill.

title: layered potato salad
directions: Begin with layer of shredded cabbage in bowl.
Add layer of sliced potatoes.
Salt, pepper and sprinkle with celery seed.
Add onion rings and pepper rings.
Add sliced eggs and spread mayonnaise over all, covering all of mixture.
Must be refrigerated 24 hours before serving.
Toss well before serving.

title: broccoli and cavetelli
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add garlic and saute until cooked.
Add mushrooms and heat until hot.
Add salt and pepper to taste as well as garlic powder (I never measure; probably 2 tablespoons); set aside.
Cook cavetelli and broccoli according to package directions.
Drain cavetelli and put in large mixing bowl. Add broccoli.
Pour butter sauce over and stir until cavetelli is coated.
Add Parmesan/Romano cheese.
Stir.
Enjoy!

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Place pepper halves on a paper towel.
Cook in microwave oven 5 to 7 minutes or until soft but still keep their shapes.
Combine onion and beef in an 8-inch round glass cake dish.
Cook in microwave oven 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until meat is no longer pink and onion is soft.
Stir several times during cooking. Combine beef mixture, rice, half of tomato sauce, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Divide filling between 6 pepper halves and place in 8-inch round glass cake dish used to cook meat in.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top.
Cover with wax paper. Cook in microwave oven 9 to 11 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: fat-free spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Grease an oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Coarsely chop apples; mix with sugar and let stand.
Start oven preheating to moderate 350°.

title: peanut butter cookie clusters
directions: Place in saucepan the salt, sugar, milk and butter.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat and add the peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until smooth. Add the oatmeal and mix well.
Cool until mixture begins to hold its shape.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Cookies harden as they cool.

title: avocado and smoked salmon soup
directions: Peel and pit the avocados and in a blender, blend them with the lemon juice, the sour cream, 3 cups of the broth and the Tabasco until the mixture is smooth, adding enough of the remaining broth to thin the mixture to the desired consistency. Transfer the soup to a bowl; season it with salt and pepper and chill it, its surface covered with plastic wrap, for 1 hour or until it is cold.
(The soup will discolor if kept for more than 6 hours.)
Stir half the salmon, chopped, into the soup; divide the soup among chilled bowls and garnish with remaining salmon, cut into strips.
Makes about 5 cups, serving 6.

title: toast
directions: Plug in toaster into the electricty.
Remove wire tie from bread wrapper.
Remove 2 slices of bread from the loaf of bread. Adjust toaster to the desired level.
Depress handle and wait. When toaster ejects, apply desired toppings accordingly.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Toss crushed cereal with the remaining 1/4 cup butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.
Good for brunch, breakfast or dinner.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, melt margarine with hot water. Place in a mixing bowl.
Add sugar and beat well with a fork. Cool.
Add egg and vanilla; beat again.

title: veal with wine sauce
directions: Pierce pastry thoroughly with fork.
Bake in 375° oven 10 minutes; remove.
In large bowl, toss together next 3 ingredients; spoon into pastry.
In bowl, stir together remaining ingredients. Slowly spoon over tuna.

title: jennifer's rocky road fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine.
In a small bowl, beat the eggs.
Add eggs, vanilla and sugar to skillet.
Stir until blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and marshmallows.
Pour into buttered pan.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Heat caramels and liquid until melted.
Stir until smooth.

title: baked chicken sandwiches
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Mix together chicken, soup, gravy, pimento and scallions; chill.
Spread chicken mixture on bread. Wrap and freeze.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Beat ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by spoon on hot greased griddle.
Brown on both sides.
Serve warm with jam or powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Double the recipe for pumpkin pie on Libby's large can, but use only 1 (13 ounce) can milk.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Sprinkle 1 package dry yellow cake mix over top of pumpkin mix. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and 1 cube margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli or beans slightly; drain and place in bottom of baking dish.
Top with the cooked chicken.
Mix soup, salad dressing, lemon juice and curry powder.
Spoon over chicken. Combine bread crumbs, melted margarine and cheese, then top over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: date rice krispies
directions: Boil dates, sugar, salt, oleo and egg 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: crystal tropical splash
directions: Juice the fruit.
Stir in sugar and pineapple juice; chill and serve.
Makes a spritzer!
Add a 2-liter bottle of lemon-lime soda to the juice just before serving or add a splash of soda to a glass of juice.

title: country corn bread
directions: Measure corn meal, salt and soda in bowl.
Add beaten egg and buttermilk.
Stir well.
Heat cooking oil in cast-iron skillet. Pour small amount of oil into corn bread mixture; stir.
Pour mixture into remaining oil in hot skillet.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for about 20 minutes or until brown on top.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute oil, flour and onion to tan.
Add celery, green pepper, water and tomato sauce.
Add seasonings to taste.
Cook until done; add shrimp and mushrooms.
Just bring to boil and take off fire and serve over rice.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Gradually add flour until it is well blended.
Form into a large ball.
Line a baking sheet with parchment or waxed paper.
Place ball onto paper and pat into a square approximately 1/2-inch thick.
Score the shortbread into long strips.
Divide the strips into "fingers."
Using a fork, generously prick over the entire surface.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut into fingers while still warm.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs.
Sift flour before measuring twice.
Add all spices to flour. Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to flour mixture.
Put everything together, mixing well.
Flour raisins and nuts; add to mixture and stir.
Add jam; mix well with spoon.
Put into 2 (9-inch) pans or Bundt pan; bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Very good plain.

title: tangy vegetable dip
directions: Measure all ingredients into a bowl.
Beat until smooth.

title: beef brisket
directions: Cook 2 1/2 hours at 250°.
Cool and slice thin.
Cook 2 1/2 hours at 250°.
Serve.

title: granny ruth's chocolate pound cake
directions: In one bowl, mix eggs until fluffy.
In another bowl, cream shortening, sugar and butter together.
Then alternate cocoa, flour, eggs and milk with sugar mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and pat dry spinach.
Add bacon, diced egg and onion. Combine Crisco oil and remaining ingredients in a screw-top jar. Cover tightly; shake vigorously to blend well.
Pour dressing over spinach mixture; toss lightly to coat evenly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pennywise beef pot roast
directions: Place pot roast on rack in Dutch oven or roasting pan. Combine mushroom mix, apricots and salt and spread over roast. Cover tightly and cook in slow oven (325°) for 2 hours.

title: red applesauce
directions: Heat applesauce.
Add red hots; stir until they melt.
Add nutmeg to taste.
Cool.
Pour applesauce back into original jar and add cinnamon stick.
Keep refrigerated.
Good with toast for breakfast.
Also makes a nice little gift.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a large
bowl, alternate the following ingredients: lettuce, celery, green pepper, peas and onions.
Mix together the mayonnaise and sugar and spread on top of these layers.
Do not mix.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon over the mayonnaise, cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Add a layer of cooked ham, beef or chicken to use as a main course.
Serves 6 - 8 people.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Fry the bacon and sausage slowly until crackling.
Remove cracklings from pan.
In the hot grease, slowly work the flour until it is a very, very dark brown.
Do not burn.
This is a slow process, but if it does scorch, throw it away and start over.
It must be dark brown but not burned.
Now add the chopped onions, stirring constantly until they are transparent.
Add chopped green pepper and saute with onion until soft.
Add the can of tomato sauce.
Work this in with roux, onions and green peppers.

title: sliced cucumbers and onions
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion and put in bowl.
Salt and let set for 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Drain liquid off and add sliced green peppers.
Use as many green peppers as you like.
Boil sugar, vinegar, water and some celery seed.
Cool well and pour over cucumber; mix and chill.
Keeps well in refrigerator for a few days.

title: microwave cheezy broccoli
directions: Place unopened packages of broccoli on end in microwave oven. Microwave
on
High
4 to 5 minutes, turning over after 2 minutes.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugars and spices together.
Put into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle over the top the cake mix (dry) and the chopped nuts.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Best served warm with Cool Whip.

title: hint of mint coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Butter an 8-inch square pan. Combine baking mix, sugar, egg, yogurt, oil, and butter flavoring. Beat until well blended. This will be a thick batter. Spoon about half of the batter into the pan and spread to cover bottom of pan. Combine the cookie crumbs and walnuts and sprinkle over the batter. Drop dollops of the remaining batter on top of the cookie crumbs and carefully spread to connect the dollops of batter. You do not have to cover all the crumbs with the batter. Bake for about 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of coffeecake. Combine the confectioners' sugar and milk. Beat until smooth. Drizzle over top of coffeecake. Allow to cool slightly before cutting.

title: cookie treat
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until light and smooth.
Slice 1 package of cookies (pinwheel fashion) about 1 inch thick.
Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread mixture over cookies.
Slice second roll of chocolate chip cookies, then cover the mixture with cookies.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate.
Serve when cool.

title: shrimp and corn chowder
directions: In saucepan, cook onions with garlic and pepper in butter until tender.
Blend in soup, cream cheese and milk; add shrimp and corn.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: banana custard
directions: Combine milk, eggs and sugar in saucepan. Cook over low heat until mixture thickens (do not boil), stirring constantly. Stir in extract and spoon custard into 4 dessert dishes.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour. Before serving, melt jelly and stir in diced banana. Spoon 1/4 of jelly mixture on top of each custard. Serves 4.
Contains 210 calories.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Sift cake mix and jello together.
Add oil.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Blend in strawberries.
Bake in baking dish or pan at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: plucketts or pull-aparts
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine the sugar, butter and salt to the scalded milk; when lukewarm, add the dissolved yeast, eggs and just enough flour to make stiff batter.
Cover and let rise until doubled, punch down and let rise again.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip each ball in melted butter, then in a mixture of brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Put in tube pan and let rise.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; lower heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately and serve warm.

title: turkey "everything"
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.

In a large bowl, combine the turkey, celery, rice, almonds, green pepper, onion, lime juice, salt and black pepper. In a medium size bowl, combine the mayonnaise and mushroom soup. Add to the turkey mixture and stir to combine all the ingredients.
Pour the mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger well.
Add oregano, salt and pepper.
Add chili beans.
Start with handful of Fritos on your plate, then hamburger mixture, cheese, onion, green peppers, lettuce and tomato.
Pour taco sauce on top.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter. Pour over other ingredients that have been well mixed. Put in loaf or tube pan and leave 2 weeks in icebox. Take out of pan and wrap in wax paper or foil and leave in icebox.

title: sorry cookies
directions: Mix and
pour
into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: turnip greens and chicken
directions: Put greens in large pot with water. Add bony pieces of chicken such as wings, necks and ribs. Season with salt, pepper and shortening. Cook all together until done.

title: pepper steak
directions: In hot oil, saute garlic, salt, ginger and pepper until garlic is golden.
Add meat and brown for 2 minutes.
Remove meat from pan.
Add green peppers and onions; cook 3 minutes.
Mix water with cornstarch and add to mixture.
Return meat to the pan and add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer until thick.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 6.

title: ugly cookies
directions: Mix milk, nuts and raisins.
Cook over low heat 4 minutes. Spread over Ritz crackers and bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Cool. Spread with frosting.

title: sugar-free lemon cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Bake pie crusts according to package directions.
Set aside to cool.
Bring water to boil and add to gelatin.
It is important to stir well until thoroughly dissolved.
Add milk to pudding mix and blend according to package directions.
Add dissolved gelatin and cream cheese to pudding mix and beat with mixer until blended.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix and cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serves 4.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: Brown meats; drain.
Put in crock-pot with cheese and salsa. When cheese is melted and hot, enjoy with corn chips.

title: orange upside-down french toast
directions: Put margarine in 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan and melt in a warm oven.
Mix next 3 ingredients and sprinkle evenly in the pan.
Mix eggs and orange juice.
Dip bread in the mixture, soaking well. Arrange evenly in pan and spoon any remaining mixture on bread. Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.
Let stand one minute.
Lift pieces onto platter, sugar side up.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape in loaves.
Place in shallow pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: orange muffins
directions: Spray muffin tin with nonstick cooking spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the biscuit mix and orange juice.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine the powdered sugar and milk until smooth.
Drizzle over the warm muffins.
If desired, poke a hole in the baked muffin and fill the center with the gooey glaze.
Makes one dozen.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Dough:
Cream together the brown sugar, shortening and eggs, then add flour to make dough to handle.
Roll 1/4-inch thick and spread with filling.

title: hickory nut pie(over 50 years old)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in unbaked pie shell.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain on paper towel.
Put into casserole.
Add tomato soup, milk mixture and 1 can string beans, drained.
Top with mashed potatoes and bake in 350°
oven about 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: diced veal and mushrooms in gravy
directions: Slice mushrooms.
Saute with onion and green pepper in skillet.
Add gravy; simmer for 10 minutes.
Thin with a little water, if necessary.
Add meat; simmer gently until meat is heated.
Serve on noodles, rice, biscuits or toasted bread cups.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, lightly beat eggs, then cream in sugar.
Add milk, oil and vanilla to the egg and sugar mixture, mixing well.
Gradually add the sifted dry ingredients as you beat at medium speed; do not overmix.
Pour cake mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Cake will be lightly golden brown and toothpick inserted in center should come out clean.
Serves 15.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over skinned chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is enough sauce for 12 chicken breasts.

title: lemon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients by hand.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 55 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and boil potatoes.
Mash potatoes, mixing in all other ingredients until well blended.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: baked greek chicken
directions: Rub each piece of chicken with small amount of olive oil and place in dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 1 1/2 hrs.

title: praline pumpkin pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water in saucepan. Place over low heat. Stir until gelatin dissolves, 2 or 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Add brown sugar and stir until dissolved.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and pour in baking dish.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients (except ketchup) in bowl.
Pour into loaf pan.
Spread ketchup on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream nut pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add
eggs, one at a time. Alternate flour and sour cream, starting and ending with flour. Mix soda with last of sour cream.
Coat nuts with flour before adding.
Add other ingredients.
Bake
at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit-filled oatmeal bars
directions: Combine in a mixing bowl flour, oats, brown sugar and baking soda.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Reserve 1/2 cup of the flour mixture.
Press remaining flour mixture into the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan. Spread with preserves.
Sprinkle with reserved flour mixture. Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes or until top is golden.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: grape pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop into shallow grease to form patties.
Fry until brown on both sides.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Place 1/2 pound caramels, 1/2 cup water and 1/4 cup margarine in top of double boiler.
Heat, stirring frequently, until caramels are melted and sauce is smooth.
Combine 2 slightly beaten eggs, 3/4 cup sugar, salt and vanilla.
Gradually add the caramel sauce, mixing well.
Add pecans.
Pour into an 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Blend all ingredients together and puree.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together shortening and sugar; add molasses and mix well.
Add sour milk and mix well; add egg and mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, nutmeg, ginger and cinnamon.
Add to shortening and sugar mixture; blend well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake until done, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
If desired, may be topped with Dream Whip (prepared according to package) before serving.

title: banana butter
directions: Mash bananas thoroughly. Measure 4 cups into 4 to 6-quart kettle.
Add sugar, lemon juice, cherries and butter.
Mix well. Bring to a hard, rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer gently (uncovered) for 20 minutes, stirring often. Pour into hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust lids. Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Place frozen rolls in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar, pudding and cinnamon over top.
Drizzle the butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can add nuts if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding hot milk last.
Pour into baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together the flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in center of the dry mixture.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine applesauce, milk and cooking oil.
Add liquid to dry mixture; stir until just moistened (batter should be lumpy).
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until a wooden toothpick comes out clean.

title: pineapple-cream cheese and nuts
directions: Mix well!
Makes enough for 2 loaves of bread.
Cut into 4 or 5 long strips.

title: tuna-zucchini bake
directions: In large
saucepan
cook zucchini, mushrooms, onion and green pepper in small
amount
of
boiling
water
for
4 to 5 minutes or until
crisp-tender.
Drain well and set aside.	In same saucepan combine soup and cornstarch; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook
and
stir
to
2 minutes more. Remove from heat.
Gently
stir
in cottage cheese, tuna, dill weed, garlic powder
and
cooked vegetables.
Turn into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch
baking dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella, Parmesan and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Let
stand
minutes before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: phil's glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling, salted water for 10 minutes.
When tender, drain; set aside.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Combine sugar, water and honey in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Cook until it forms soft ball stage (235° on a candy thermometer). Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Dip pecans into syrup; place on wax paper to cool.

title: applesauce, cottage cheese salad
directions: Boil water and applesauce.
Pour over jello.
Put half of mixture in mold.
Place in refrigerator to set.
Soak gelatin in water.
Dissolve in hot water.
Add cottage cheese, celery and mayonnaise. When applesauce mixture has started to set pour this on and add remainder of applesauce mixture. Return to refrigerator to mold.
Serves 8.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix whipping cream and light brown sugar in an 8 cup bowl. Put in the microwave on full power for 12 minutes.
Do not stir. Take out and add butter and pecans.
Drop by spoon on aluminum foil.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Measure each cup of oatmeal in blender and grind, then stir by hand into cookie dough.
Grind candy bar in blender and add to cookie dough. Stir in chocolate chips.
Roll into ping-pong size balls.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Grease frozen bread.
Cover and let rise to double in size.
Punch down and roll out on floured board to 15 x 19-inches.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Brush over dough.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over dough.
Roll up.
Punch to close; cut to make 12 buns.
Grease baking dish. Pour 1/2 of the following on bottom.
Add buns and pour remaining over top.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O
in water.
Add fruit and nuts.
Place 1/2 of mixture in 8 x 11-inch dish.
Let set in refrigerator, leaving remainder
set
at room temperature.
When mixture in refrigerator sets, spread
sour
cream
over
top and then add remaining mixture.
Return to refrigerator.

title: aunt robbie's pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in tube pan. Start with cold oven and bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: spaghetti pork chops
directions: Brown meat in flour and oil.
Spread one can of soup in bottom of dish.
Layer pork chops, pepper and onion slices.

title: baked stuffed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	Wash
chops
and
pat dry.
Mix crumbs, onions, celery,
parsley,
salt and wheat germ.
Stuff when moistened with
enough
milk to hold together.
Brown the chops in butter in a hot heavy pan with a tightly fitting lid. Add stock.
Cover and
bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.	Serves 4.

title: ripe tomato pickles
directions: Boil 3 hours.
Put in jars and seal.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mix together butter and sugar with your hands.
Add vanilla and work in well.
Add milk if mixture is too dry.

title: pineapple-cheese cake(diet)
directions: Place eggs, lemon juice, vanilla, sweeteners and half of cottage cheese in blender.
Blend.
Add other half of cottage cheese and blend.
Add ice cubes one at a time.
In saucepan, sprinkle gelatine over juice until dissolved.
Add to blender mixture.
Blend.
Add pineapple.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan. I sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs; add next 3 ingredients.
Stir in dry ingredients. Pour into well-greased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours (cake pan baking time will not be as long).

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix together; save some crumbs for topping along with butter. Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Makes a large dish.

title: lasagne
directions: Fry and drain beef; add sauce.
While doing this, boil water and add noodles.
Cook until just tender; fork during cooking to separate.
Drain noodles.
Cool with cold water.
Make sure they are drained well.
Now place a layer of noodles in an 8 x 10-inch pan (or smaller if you would like more layers).
Now add sauce layer and then cottage cheese; spread thinly.
Now add Mozzarella cheese.
Continue layers until gone.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; then cool 10 minutes.
This gives it more flavor.

title: date balls
directions: Melt
butter
in
saucepan
over
low heat.
Add sugar. Stir until
mixed well.	Beat egg.
Add a small amount of hot mixture to egg.
Put warmed egg back in saucepan.
Add vanilla and dates. Cook until dates are completely broken up.	Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes.
Mix Rice Krispies and nuts in a mixing bowl.
Add cooked
mixture
and
mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.
It is easier to shape ball if you put butter on your hands.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown meat in oil in heated skillet.
In large roasting pan, mix soy sauce, coffee, bay leaves, garlic, oregano and one sliced onion.
Transfer meat to roasting pan.
Top with second sliced onion.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for 3 1/2 to 4 hours, basting every hour with pan juices.
If liquid begins to boil away, add another cup of coffee and a splash of soy sauce.
Serve with pan juices.

title: health burgers
directions: Heat lentils, water and salt to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash.

title: hamburg quiche
directions: Brown meat and drain grease.
Blend next four ingredients. Stir in meat, cheese, onion and pepper. Put in pie shells.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Heat together cream of chicken soup, water and 1/4 cup margarine.
Add potatoes, cheese, onion and sour cream.
Mix well. Put into casserole dish.
Mix corn flakes and 1/4 melted margarine.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cover loosely with foil for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together. Fold in nuts and chocolate chips. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes (test a few minutes before; if not done, continue baking). Will be done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Put 7-Up and Hawaiian Punch in bowl.
Drop scoops of sherbet in bowl.
Serve.

title: batter for shrimp or fish
directions: Wash, drain and dry shrimp or fish with paper towels.

title: old-fashioned pot roast
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
In Dutch oven, heat trimmings until 1 tablespoon fat accumulates.
Discard trimmings.
Rub meat with 2 tablespoons flour. Brown the meat in hot fat.
Season with salt, marjoram, thyme, basil and pepper.
Add sliced onion and 1 cup water.
Cover and cook at 350° for 2 hours. Add vegetables and 1/2 cup water. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cover and cook until meat and vegetables are tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove to warm platter.

title: yummies
directions: Measure the peanut butter, vanilla, oats and salt.
In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, margarine, cocoa, and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from fire and quickly add the peanut butter, vanilla, oats and salt.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Allow to cool.
Mixture will harden quickly.

title: dressing
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and poultry seasoning.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Add celery, onion and oil.
Pour in a large iron skillet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
In a large bowl mix with salted broth.
Add turkey or chicken if desired.
Mix well and place in a large, greased baking dish.
Keep covered and stored in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Before serving, heat in oven until slightly brown and hot.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in deep baking dish.
Mix Bisquick, sugar and milk.
Pour batter into margarine in dish.
Place fruit over top of mixture; do not stir.

title: pineapple whip
directions: Mix 1 can crushed pineapple (undrained) and stir in package of vanilla pudding together in a bowl.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour in crust and let set for at least 2 hours.
Then serve.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Slice raisin bread into 3/4-inch pieces.
Place in shallow buttered 1-quart baking dish; set aside.
Heat milk with butter until hot and butter is melted (do not allow to boil).
Beat eggs with vanilla, salt and sugar.
Add hot milk mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour over bread.
Allow to stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set baking dish in pan of hot water to half the depth of dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 50 minutes, or until custard is set.

title: chili egg puff
directions: Beat eggs in mixer until lemon colored and light.
Add all other ingredients except cheese and chilies and blend.
Stir in chilies and cheese and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until top is lightly browned and center appears firm.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples; slice and place in a pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.

title: fried corn
directions: Remove corn from cob.
Mix sugar, salt, flour and water.
Add corn and place in skillet with bacon grease. Cook about 20 minutes, stirring often. Before serving, crumble bacon over top.

title: easy sweet milk pancakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine the dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Beat thoroughly.
These will be light and fluffy.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in sheet pan.
Place holes in cake while still warm.
When cooled, bring to a boil the pineapple and sugar and pour over cake when cooled.
Mix pudding mix as directed and spread over cake.
Finish by spreading Cool Whip and coconut.

title: country captain
directions: Cut chicken into bite size chunks.
Brown chicken in margarine until just browned.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato liquid, onion and curry powder.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: marinated beef roast(8 servings)
directions: Place roast in a deep bowl.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and marinate, refrigerated, overnight. Mount and balance roast on rotisserie spit.
Cook 3 to 4 inches from medium-hot coals for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven until inserted knife comes out clean.
Use meringue or pecan halves on top.

title: spanish style green beans
directions: Microwave, or steam beans until crisp tender. Heat
olive oil in wok or large skillet until
hot.
Add parcooked green beans and saute until a bit browned.
Add garlic, cumin, and pepper.
Saute another minute. Add bread crumbs and combine until completely coated and warmed through, about another minute.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually beat in oil and sugar.
Add grated zucchini, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and powder, mixing well.
Gradually blend in flour, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into greased Bundt pan or 2 (9 5/8 x 5 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch) loaf pans.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mom's green stuff
directions: In bowl, combine Cool Whip, pudding mix and pineapple.
Mix well and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: marshmallow fruit salad
directions: In a large serving bowl combine marshmallows, coconut, oranges, pineapple, grapes, nuts and salt.
Mix to cover with sour cream.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve chilled.

title: crumb cake
directions: Grease or spray with Pam an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together, except pie filling with pastry blender until crumbly. Spread out half of the crumbly mix in pan.
Then spread out pie filling mix.
Then spread out other half of crumbly mix on top layer and bake at 370° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all the dry ingredients together.
Mix in the pumpkin, oil, water and eggs until thoroughly combined.
Stir in the nuts. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool on a rack in the pans for 10 minutes.
Then remove from the pans onto a rack to cool completely.

title: cheese and ham casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Combine with ham in 8 x 10-inch greased casserole.
Mix beaten eggs and milk.
Add cheese and crackers to casserole, then milk and egg mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt bea's fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Allow to chill for 1 hour.
Makes a great holiday salad.

title: okra a la cross creek
directions: Have ready boiling, lightly salted water.
Choose only tiny very young fresh okra pods.
Wash.
Do not cut off the stem end, as you trust me.
Drop whole pods in rapidly boiling water and boil exactly seven minutes from the time the water resumes its boiling. Not a moment longer.
Drain quickly.
Arrange like the spokes of a wheel on hot individual serving dishes.
Place individual bowls of Hollandaise in the centers of the dishes.
The okra is eaten as one eats unhulled strawberries, lifting with the fingers by the stem end and dipping into Hollandaise.
I recommend this to those who think they don't like okra.
It is firm, not slimy and with the sauce, superb.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Saut the crumbled up sausage in large skillet, then drain. Add and saut until crisp-tender the celery, onion and green pepper. Remove from heat and add the water chestnuts and slivered almonds. Cook the rice in water, dry chicken noodle soup mix and herbs of choice. Combine all in ovenproof casserole and bake at 350° until heated through. May need to add more water if reheated later.

title: taco cups
directions: In medium skillet over medium heat, brown ground beef.
Drain off excess grease.
Add barbecue sauce, chopped onion, chopped garlic and brown sugar.
Mix well until a paste like consistency. Spray muffin pan with vegetable spray.
Line muffin cups with biscuits.
Fill each cup with mixture.
Top with shredded Cheddar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, peppers, celery and mushrooms in shortening.
Add salt, chili powder and pepper.
Add tomatoes, sauce and kidney beans.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Melt margarine and mix with garlic. Brush over warm biscuits.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and then add pecans.
Pour into 1 unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, then lower heat to 300° and bake for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: red hot chili
directions: Brown ground beef and diced onions in skillet.
Add chili powder and salt.

title: shrimp and crab mold
directions: Mix together cream cheese and mushroom soup together in large bowl.
Microwave until warm and melted together.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, onion and margarine in chicken stock until potatoes are tender.
Blend flour with small amount of water to make paste.
Add with corn and chicken to potato mixture.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add milk, salt and pepper and heat to serving temperature.

title: tomato and cucumber summer salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth.
With blender on high, gradually add oil in a slow, steady stream.
Stir in parsley.
Cover dressing and chill.
Arrange lettuce on chilled salad plates.
Top with tomato and cucumber slices.
Drizzle with dressing.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 3 floured cake pans. Bake at 350° until done, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dell's refried beans
directions: Cook beans until mushy with oil. Fry bacon crisp, cool and crumble. Save bacon grease. Mash or blend beans until smooth. Add bacon, salt and pepper, to taste. Add bacon grease and blend again, or mash.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all items except bologna in large pot and cook for 2 hours on medium heat.
Place bologna in pot and cook for another 20 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of the butter.
Add onion.
Cook and stir until golden.
Sprinkle beef strips with salt and brown over high heat on both sides.
Remove and reduce heat.
Melt remaining butter. Cook mushroom slices turning frequently.
Season mushroom slices with nutmeg.
Return beef strips.
Blend liquid gravy seasoning into sour cream.	Stir in.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate cheeses and mix together.
Shock the broccoli in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
In a bowl toss broccoli in tablespoon of olive oil.
Take pizza crust and rub lightly with olive oil until it shines.
Spread crust with cheese. Top cheese with prepared broccoli.
Sprinkle with oregano and garlic to taste.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Brush chicken with Miracle Whip; coat with combination of remaining ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix and set aside.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Scoop level tablespoonfuls and roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 18 minutes. Remove when done; let cool.

title: cranberry sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour ingredients over chicken and cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with rice.

title: hot beef spread
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and milk.
Stir in dried beef, onion, green pepper and pepper; mix well.
Stir in sour cream. Spoon into an 8-inch pie plate or shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with assorted crackers.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Mix together:
flour, brown sugar, shortening and salt, forming a crumbly meal.
Set aside 1/2 cup of this.

title: rice croquettes
directions: You will need:
3/4 bushel fresh red chile, string or twine and sisal rope.

title: beer party pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl; add pretzels. Place in roaster and bake at 350° for 3 hours, turning every 1/2 hour.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into pie crust.
Cover with top crust, crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: creamy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 8 to 9 minutes in microwave.
Place in shallow dish.
Mix soup, milk, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Sprinkle lemon juice over broccoli.
Pour soup mixture over broccoli.
Pour soup mixture over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is bubbly.

title: sue's sensational salad
directions: *To toast almonds, bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: crabmeat and hot cheese appetizers
directions: Mic crabmeat, onion, pepper, celery, mayonnaise and cheese together.
Cut English muffin open and lightly toast.
Then pile on mixture and put under broiler until bubbly.
Cut each half of English muffin into quarters and serve.

title: salsa
directions: Dip tomatoes in boiling water 30 seconds.
Dip in cold water and slip off skins.
Core and chop tomatoes.
In 6-quart kettle combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil, stirring often.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes or to desired thickness.
Fill hot jars with salsa, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Run a spatula down to remove bubbles.
Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes.
Yield: 6 pints.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and vinegar in saucepan.
Add half the juice from a can of diced, sliced or tiny whole beets.
Stir well. Heat to a boil slowly, stirring constantly.
Add drained beets. (A little grated orange rind makes a nice flavor addition.)

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients, adding one at a time.
Bake 1 hour at 325°, until well browned.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay out rolls on cookie sheet or jelly roll pan to form a crust.
Press "seams" in dough.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, approximately 15 minutes.
Cool.
Beat together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread over cooled crust. Spread finely cut vegetables on top of cream cheese layer. Sprinkle cheese over all.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Press lightly to "settle" vegies and cheese into cream cheese layer.
Store in refrigerator.
Good made day ahead.
Cut into small squares to serve.
May garnish before serving with small cherry tomatoes or cucumber slice.

title: "mississippi mud"
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients, except Marshmallow Creme, and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Leave in pan and, while hot, spread Marshmallow Creme on cake.
Put back in oven; watch closely.
When marshmallow is running smooth, take out (only takes a few minutes).
Let cake cool and spread with Betty Crocker canned frosting.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until tender.
While potatoes are cooking in separate pot, saute onions in butter until tender.
Turn off heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper and stir to blend.
Add drained whole corn, creamed corn, milk and ham.
Turn heat back on and bring just to a simmer.
Stir frequently to keep milk from scorching.
While waiting for chowder to come to a simmer, drain potatoes and add to chowder.
Corn bread goes well with this soup.

title: special broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Chop, if desired.
Add remaining ingredients and stir together.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; stir well.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine cornflakes and 1/4 cup melted butter. Sprinkle evenly over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender; drain fat.
Stir in beans, soup, water, 3/4 teaspoon of salt and 1/8 teaspoon of pepper.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Stir Cool Whip and milk together.
Add lemonade to mixture. Stir well and pour into pie crust.

title: peach barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together.
Let stand to blend for an hour or so.
Use with barbecue, spareribs or chicken; also for a pork loin roast.

title: chocolate chip pecan fudge
directions: Melt in microwave oven. Add 3/4 cup semi-sweet chocolate bits and 3/4 cup coarse pecans or walnuts. Chill 1 hour.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix together.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Mix and heat all ingredients.
Add to cooked and drained carrots.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.

title: chili beef n' biscuit bake
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef, onion and pepper; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Add 1/2 sauce can of water, simmer while preparing dough.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press with fork. Bake at 350 for 12 - 15 minutes.

title: tortilla snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tortillas.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll and chill 1 hour.
Slice and serve.
Discard ends.

title: date pudding
directions: Boil 1 1/2 cups brown sugar and 1 1/2 cups water about 5 minutes.
Cool.
Prepare batter, mixing first 8 ingredients.
Pour cooled brown sugar mixture into square baking pan and pour batter on top.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve warm or cool topped with whipped cream.

title: reception salad
directions: Let juice from pineapple come to boil; pour over jello; stir to dissolve.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, add pineapple, nuts, salt and cream cheese.
Blend well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Let set overnight.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in Crisco oil.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Season to taste.
Place in a covered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion.
Drain. Boil noodles in a large pan. Drain.
Mix all ingredients together in a large pan except the cheese.
Simmer on low approximately 10 minutes or until warm.
Add cheese. Stir and serve.

title: crispy vegetable appetizer tree
directions: Wash endive, lettuce or parsley and dry well.
Attach greens to cone.
Start from bottom and work upwards.
Use toothpicks for the greens.
Do likewise with the assorted vegetables and insert in the tree for decorations.
Arrange the remaining vegetable dippers on serving plate around the base of tree.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: butternut squash bake
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir in squash (mixture will be thin).
Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until almost set.
Combine topping.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes or until bubbly.

title: turkey delight casserole
directions: Brown almonds and corn flakes in butter.
Pour in bottom of greased casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Then pour remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: texas hot chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain well.
Put beef, onion, tomato sauce, water, kidney beans, and all spices into a large pot.
In small dish, mix flour and enough water to make paste. Stir into chili.
Cover and simmer on low heat for a couple of hours.
It is best on the next day.
Serves 10 people.

title: chicken wing sauce
directions: Mix ingredients; soak chicken for 2 to	3
hours.
Deep fry.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Pound chicken breast until thin.
Put about 1 to 2 tablespoons Rice-A-Roni at widest edge.
Roll chicken around rice and roll in bread crumbs.
Drizzle oil over breaded chicken.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Wash and cut tomatoes into quarters and slice very thin.
Put into bowl and stir in raisins, lemon rind, juice, vinegar and salt.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on bottom of pie shell.
Mix sugar, flour and spices.
Add to tomatoes.
Pour into pie crust and dot with butter.
Lay on top crust and crimp edges.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Mix all ingredients and press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; grease pan lightly.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool slightly and cut into squares.

title: asparagus
directions: Place asparagus and mixture of all other ingredients in Ziploc bag.
Let marinate.
Serve at room temperature.
Amount of marinade you need will depend on the amount of asparagus you prepare.

title: clam balls
directions: Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: gouda cheese puff
directions: Remove dough. Unroll dough and press together to make a square.

title: breakfast egg bake
directions: In large bowl, lightly toss cheeses together.
Sprinkle half of cheese mixture in lightly greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
In medium skillet, cook mushrooms, green onions, and bell pepper in margarine until onions and pepper are tender.
Arrange vegetables over cheese.
Arrange ham or sausage over vegetables.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over meat.
(To make ahead, prepare to this point.
Cover and refrigerate.)
Heat oven to 350 degrees. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl using wire whisk, blend flour, milk, and eggs.
Pour over layers in baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes or until mixture is set and top is lightly browned.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.
12 servings.

title: date pudding
directions: Put eggs, sugar and cream into mixing bowl.
Beat until creamy. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to nuts and dates.
Stir until nuts and dates are covered with batter. Turn into greased baking dish and bake in slow oven at 250° to 275° about 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: low-fat manicotti supreme
directions: Mix cheeses and spices; set aside.
Put manicotti shells in boiling water.
Boil for only 5 minutes.
Pour out half of the boiling water; replace with cold water so it is just warm to your touch.
Keep shells in this water or else they will dry out and crack.
Remove one shell at a time and stuff, using a butter knife, with cheese and spice mixture.
Spread approximately 1/2 cup of the spaghetti sauce into a 9-inch casserole dish.
Fill with stuffed manicotti shells.
Pour remaining spaghetti sauce over stuffed shells, being sure to cover them completely.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: kentucky jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well. Combine dry ingredients.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with buttermilk and coffee.
Stir in jam.
Bake in three 8-inch pans at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: red chili sauce(this recipe to be used with chicken enchiladas.)
directions: Melt shortening in medium skillet.
Add rest of ingredients; stir until blended.
Gradually stir in 2 cups water.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, flour and butter in pot.
Cook on low until butter is melted; stir while cooking.
Remove from stove.
Add eggs and pecans; mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bertucci's vegetable chicken chowder
directions: In a large stock pot (2 gallon), melt the butter over low heat.
Add flour and mix to obtain a paste.
Do not burn.

title: hopscotch candy
directions: Combine peanut butter, butterscotch chips and marshmallows
in top
of
double
boiler
over hot water.
Melt, then remove
from heat;
stir
in
noodles that have been crushed. Leave
in double boiler while you drop candy from fork.
Takes a few hours to set.

title: green spaghetti
directions: Steam the fresh spinach until just wilted or the frozen until warm.
Put spinach and its liquid into blender.
Add warm broth and liquify.
Stir cheese and milk into puree.
Toss spaghetti with butter, then with green sauce.

title: brunch quesadillas with fruit salsa
directions: Make fruit salsa; combine fruits, honey and cilantro.
Set aside.

title: chicken-italian dressing bake
directions: Combine breadcrumbs, cheese and salt in a plastic bag; shake to mix.
Dip chicken in salad dressing.
Place 1 piece of chicken in bag and shake to coat.
Repeat procedure with remaining chicken. Place in lightly greased pan (use Pam vegetable cooking spray). Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Spray chicken with cooking spray and bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in airtight container and label "Spiced Tea."
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of Spiced Tea mixture.
Add boiling water.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir into buttermilk. Add buttermilk mixture to dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Cover and chill.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until soft; let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in baking dish.
Combine dry ingredients and add butter.
Mix and sprinkle crumbly mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until nicely browned.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate graham cracker marshmallow bars
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and marshmallows.
In a double boiler melt Baker's chocolate.
Add sugar and canned milk.
Cook until thick like custard, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Add butter, salt and vanilla.
Cool.
Pour over marshmallow mixture.
Sprinkle crumbs over a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put mixture in pan and press down with back of spoon.
Sprinkle crumbs over mixture again and press again.

title: leona's congealed salad(ann maloy's)
directions: Mix well and chill.
Very good to make the night before.

title: roy's multi-grain bread
directions: Combine flour and salt in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Place molasses or honey in warm water with yeast.
Allow yeast to rise to the top then add applesauce.
Stir this mixture with flour (if making raisin bread, at this point add at least 2 cups of raisins, usually more.)
Turn onto floured board and knead 10 minutes or more.
Spray bowl with vegetable spray.
Cover and let rise at least 30 minutes.
Cut and form into 2 or 3 loaves and place in an oven preheated to 250°.
When about double in bulk turn oven up to about 350°.
Bake for about 30 to 35 minutes, depending on your oven.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookie pie
directions: Microwave marshmallows and 2 tablespoons milk in medium bowl on High for 45 seconds.
Stir.
Refrigerate 15 minutes to cool. Stir in 1 cup of the Cool Whip.
Mix 2 cups milk with pudding; beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip; spoon into crust.
Arrange cookies over pudding mixture.
Spread marshmallow mixture over cookies. Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: peanut balls
directions: Mix all together and roll into balls.

title: 2 giant cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl; divide into 2 equal parts.
Grease 2 pizza pans.
Using fingers, work mixture to one inch from edge.
Leave border in order for mixture to spread.
Bake for 30 minutes; do not overbake!
Cool for 10 minutes.
Decorate with icing.

title: special spuds
directions: Wash potatoes; cut into cubes.
Layer with onions and butter. Pour 1 cup Worcestershire sauce over cubes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 400° until done, about 1 hour.

title: beef casserole(makes 4 servings)
directions: Place green beans in a 1-quart casserole, icy side up.
Cook, covered, on High for 5 minutes.
Reserve.
Combine beef cubes and meat tenderizer in a 2 to 3-quart casserole.
Toss lightly.
Add onion.
Cook, covered, on High for 15 to 20 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add tomato soup, 1/2 cup water, noodles and green beans to beef cubes.
Stir lightly and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, covered, on High for 5 minutes.
Stir and let stand, covered, 3 to 4 minutes before serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients; bring to a rolling boil and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, raisins, onions and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli and marinate at least 2 hours; stir occasionally.

title: zucchini nut bread(microwave)
directions: Grease 6-cup microproof ring mold. Mix sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle 2 teaspoons of mix over greased surface. Beat together eggs, remaining sugar, oil, yogurt, vanilla and zucchini. Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into prepared pan.
Cook on 70% power 15 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Rotate dish if bread appears to be raising unevenly.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan. Cool completely before slicing.	Yields 12 to 18 slices.

title: mama's orange jello supreme
directions: Mix together and chill until set.

title: meringue topped grapefruit
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Halve each grapefruit; remove seeds and cut between membranes to free fruit sections.
Place on a baking sheet.
In a small pan, heat marmalade until just warm.
Beat egg whites, adding sugar one tablespoon at a time, until stiff peaks form.
Fold warm marmalade into egg whites.
Top each grapefruit, mounding the meringue and bringing it to the edges of the fruit. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until well browned.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar.
Add salt, soda, baking powder, spices, 1/2 of the flour and 1/2 of the molasses.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until cracks disappear from surface of cookies.
If moister cookie is desired, bake less time.
Makes about 40 (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: pie crust
directions: Heat oil
and water.
Cool until lukewarm. Add flour to make a ball.
Pat out in 9-inch pie pan.

title: chicken can-can
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Spread in a large, Pam-sprayed, baking dish.
Top with sauteed sliced almonds or leftover chow mein noodles.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: snickers salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, chill & serve.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Use on any type fruit.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Place on unbuttered cookie sheet.
Press top of each ball with a fork. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: sour cream fruit dip
directions: Stir together sour cream, preserves (cut up into large pieces of fruit) and cinnamon.
Chill up to 24 hours.
Serve with fruit. Makes 1 cup (8 servings).

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, milk, eggs and flour.
Pour over blueberries and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: delicious white bread(tom's favorite)
directions: Grease 2 (8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
In bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Blend well.
In saucepan, heat water and oil until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add warm liquid to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour until dough pulls cleanly away from sides of bowl.

title: coconut pecan delight and icing
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Cool in pan.
Place cake on cake dish and ice with following icing.

title: squid adobo
directions: Boil squid in garlic, vinegar, water and salt. When tender, take out squid and remove membrane, eyes and stomach.
Set 1/2 cup broth aside.
Cut squid into 1-inch pieces. Set aside.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag, put all ingredients. Close bag and shake well.
Place potatoes in a shallow baking pan.
Bake 40 minutes, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are brown and tender.
Garnish with parsley or mint.
Serves 8 people.

title: elsie's chocolate cake
directions: Cream Crisco and
sugars. Beat in eggs. Add the rest of the ingredients alternately, beating well after each addition. Pour into 9
x
12-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes,
then
the
last
minutes.
Frost as desired.

title: plum crisp
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, put seeded and quartered plums.
Blend the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and mace. Add to beaten egg and stir with fork until crumbly. Spoon over plums.
Pour melted butter over top evenly. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumber dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese (softened) with sour cream and mayonnaise until mixture is smooth.
Stir in cucumber, minced onion, cider vinegar, salt and white pepper to taste. Chill, covered, for 4 hours.
Just before serving, stir.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: slow cooked pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into 3 inch by 1 inch strips.
Brown in oil in skillet.
Transfer to slow cooker.
Combine the soy sauce, onion, garlic, sugar, salt, pepper, and ginger.
Pour over beef.
Cover and cook on low for 5-6 hours or until meat is tender.
Add tomatoes and green peppers; cook on low for 1 hour longer. Combine the cold water and corn starch to make a paste; stir into slow cooker and cook on high until thickened.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Yield:
Serves 6-8.

title: mystery salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in a large bowl. Put more nuts on top, if desired.
Cover and refrigerate until served.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients all together. Add all to apple mixture and stir well. Put in a 9 x 13 greased pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Needs no frosting, but you can sprinkle sugar and a little cinnamon on top, if desired (optional).

title: apricot chicken divine(from:  eaters choice cookbook)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover bottom of a shallow baking pan with olive oil.
Meanwhile, shake chicken in a plastic bag filled with flour and salt until chicken is coated.
Place chicken in a single layer in the baking pan and bake for 25 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add beaten eggs; mix well.
Fold in pineapple, bread cubes and milk.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for almost 1 hour. Goes well with baked ham or chicken.

title: asparagus and peas casserole
directions: Heat soup and cheese.
Alternate layers of asparagus and peas in baking dish.
Sprinkle with almonds and top with soup and cheese mixture.
Pour onions over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: lime jello cheese salad(for 16)
directions: Drain pineapple, saving liquid.
Mash cream cheese with pineapple; soften gelatin with pineapple juice.
Make jello according to directions, using only 3 cups of water.
Mix it all together; add drained grapes.
Put in oiled salad molds and chill overnight.

title: glazed smoked sausage
directions: Cut smoked sausage into 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix together mustard, lemon juice and preserves to make a glaze.
Spread sausage pieces on baking pan and brush with glaze.

title: carol's turkey meat loaf
directions: Combine the ingredients in a large bowl, except for the barbecue sauce.
Mix well; spread in loaf pan.
Cover top with Bull's Eye original barbecue sauce.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Delicious cold in sandwiches, too.

title: dr. bird cake(hummingbird cake)
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir by hand.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas, and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.
If using a bundt pan, bake 40-45 minutes.
Either icing is great on this cake.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Flour chicken and brown in oil; remove chicken.
Make roux by browning the flour in the same oil that the chicken was browned in.
Add and saute onion.
Add water and seasoned salt to taste.
Add chicken; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add mushrooms.
Continue to cook for another 20 minutes, uncovered, to reduce gravy, if desired.
Serve over rice.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: barbecue sauce fine herbs
directions: Peel and chop onions and garlic.
Saute in a bit of oil, then add to large pot with the rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil. Reduce to simmer and cook for 45 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: swiss steak
directions: Remove excess fat from steak; cut meat into 6 to 8 pieces. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; pound into both sides of meat with mallet or edge of saucer.
Brown meat in shortening in heavy skillet.
Add onion, pepper and mushrooms.
Blend ketchup and water; pour over steak.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, about 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise with a heaping teaspoonful Dijon mustard, a little pickle juice and a little milk.
Blend until mixture is slightly thinner then original mayonnaise.
Mix the dressing with the bowl of potatoes already set aside.

title: sausage casserole
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, brown sausage. Drain.
Add onions, carrot and green pepper; cook until tender. Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and begins to boil.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and sage.

title: glazed carrots(microwave)
directions: Cut carrots into long thin strips.
Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, butter, water, salt and cinnamon in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave at High until butter is melted, about 1 minute.
Stir to blend.
Stir in carrots until coated.
Cover. Microwave at High until carrots are tender, 5 to 8 minutes, stirring once.

title: elva miller's brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 450° for 5 minutes.

title: apple dessert
directions: Spread apple pie filling in 8-inch or 9-inch buttered cake pan. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add cheese to dry ingredients and mix together.
Combine all with melted butter.
Mix until crumbly. Sprinkle over apple filling.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix together
flour,
sugar,
baking
powder,
salt and baking soda.
Stir
in
orange
juice, orange peel, shortening and egg. Mix
well.	Stir
in
cranberries
and nuts.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5-inch pan;	bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done. Cool on rack 15 minutes.
Makes one loaf.

title: edie's banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together in order listed. Pour batter into standard loaf pan, heavily greased with Pam spray. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine and Hershey bars in pan.
Add whipped cream and pour into graham cracker crust.
Hide from the kids and eat after they have all gone night-night!

title: pound cake dessert
directions: Break pound cake into small pieces.
Put 1/2 pound cake in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 Cool Whip.
Top Cool Whip with 1/2 crushed Heath bars.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel the boiled sweet potatoes.
Slice them the long way and lay in Pyrex dish.
Mix the sugars and cinnamon together in a bowl. Sprinkle this mixture over the top of the sliced sweet potatoes. Cut the margarine in chunks and lay on top of the sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven until most of the sugar melts.
You might need to sprinkle a little water on top of sugar before baking.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute onions in butter in saucepan over medium heat until tender. Add precooked rice, salt, pepper and liquid.
Bring to boil uncovered.
Cover and simmer gently for 3 minutes.
Add beans to rice.
Serve with shredded sharp cheese on top.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy quiche lorraine
directions: Combine bacon, onion, eggs, sour cream, Swiss cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into quiche dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Wash and peel two medium size zucchini.
Put in blender and mix to liquefy.
When ready, add flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and baking soda. Put on blend and add raisins.

title: sweet sour pork
directions: Dip pork strips first in egg and then in flour and fry until golden brown in color; remove.
Take the broth, vinegar, sugar and soy sauce and let them boil up, then add the cornstarch.
When it starts to thicken, add the peppers and onion.
Cook very little, then add meat and let it boil up and serve immediately.

title: cheesy tuna and noodles
directions: Prepare Ramen noodle soup according to directions.
Add seasoning packets.
Drain off most of liquid; set aside.

title: star corn pudding
directions: Saute onion in butter until limp.
Blend in flour.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Stir slowly into beaten eggs.
Add corn, salt and pepper.
Wash and core tomatoes.
Cut 3 times across blossom end to within 3/4 inch of stem end.
Place in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish and open segments.
Pour corn mixture around tomatoes.
Place dish in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: pudding pie
directions: Alternately layer in 9 x 13-inch pan, graham crackers, chocolate pudding, graham crackers and vanilla pudding.
There should be 2 chocolate layers and 2 vanilla layers.
Top with layer of graham crackers with Cool Whip spread on top.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours before serving.

title: goulash
directions: In a large stir fry pan, brown beef in olive oil on high heat.
Add spices except celery powder.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add 1 can tomato sauce, mushrooms, water chestnuts, celery powder, more black pepper and chili powder to taste and cook for 5 minutes on medium temperature.
Add second can of tomato sauce and cook for 10 more minutes on low temperature.
Simmer until ready to serve over rice or noodles.
Serve 4 to 6 hearty appetites.

title: baked apple slices
directions: Place apples in a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Combine sugar, spices and the apple cider; pour over apples.
Dot with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: chocolate mint pie
directions: Mix cookies and hot water in small bowl.
Spread evenly in bottom of crust.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Add milk and peppermint extract.
Beat until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping and food coloring.
Spoon mixture into pie crust.
Smooth top with spatula.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or until set.
Garnish with a dollop of whipped topping and maraschino cherry.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Dice all; add all ingredients to potatoes and add enough milk to moisten.
Pour over this 3/4 cup melted butter.
Put in baking dish and cover top with cornflake crumbs.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: bran apple muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Melt margarine and butter. Add flour and sour cream. Beat on low with a mixer. Batter will be slightly lumpy but the flour should be mixed thoroughly into the batter. Spray muffin liners and fill each muffin cup 1/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20-30 minutes. Have an extra batch ready, because these are so good when they are warm, that everyone will want MORE!

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour gradually.
Add vanilla last.
Place in greased and floured tube pan.

title: 5 can casserole
directions: Mix together.
Add noodles just before baking.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave pudding
directions: Blend together eggs and sugar with hand mixer.
Add salt, flour and cocoa.
Slowly add milk until well blended.
Cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Blend with mixer.
Continue to microwave and blend every 2 minutes until pudding has thickened.

title: refrigerator bread and butter pickles
directions: Put sugar, vinegar, salt and spices in gallon jar and mix well, then layer in the cucumbers and onions.
Put in refrigerator.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
When cool and oleo is melted, add eggs.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup water and add to mixture.
Stir in 6 cups of flour, all at once.
Cover tightly and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Can be kept up to 5 days.
Roll on floured surface; shape or cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased pan and let rise.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 40.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Roll into balls the size of a quarter and put in the refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.
Dip balls using a toothpick into melted chocolate.
Melt chocolate in double boiler for best results.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with cut up chicken. Mix soup, milk, celery and onion and pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing, broth and margarine and sprinkle over chicken.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Leave all ingredients until they reach room temperature.
Mix well and form into ball.
Chill.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 1 large or 2 small balls.

title: danish thin pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients together until well mixed.
Preheat skillet.
Dip batter into pan (about one ladleful) and tip pan to spread out in pan.
Cook first side until edges brown.
Turn over and cook until dry.
Put on plate, folded in half.
Serve with butter, syrup, honey or jam.

title: garden vegetable chowder
directions: Cut squash lengthwise and slice into 1/4 inch slices.
Melt margarine in Dutch oven.
Stir in squash, onion, parsley and basil. Simmer 8 minutes.
Stir in flour and pepper.
Cook until bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in bouillon, lemon juice and water.
Heat, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Add corn and heat to boiling. Simmer 8 minutes.
Stir in evaporated milk and tomatoes.
Heat to almost boiling, then add cheese.
Stir constantly until melted. This is a most delicious chowder.

title: risotto
directions: Bring 6 to 8 quarts water with above ingredients (except rice and grated cheese) to a boiling point.
Skim top of water of excess fat; turn down to simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Strain broth into another pan; bring to rapid boil.
Add rice.
Cover and cook for about 20 minutes.
Add broth as needed to rice.
Spread rice on dish; sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Serve chicken and vegetables on side.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Drain liquid from the beans and put into large bowl.
Chop pepper fine and also onion.
Mix altogether.
Chill overnight or refrigerate for several hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients. Cook over medium heat until thick. Pour into precooked pie crust. Beat egg whites until they stand in peaks. Add 3 tablespoons of sugar and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla. Beat about 1 minute. Put on top of pie. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix first 4 dry ingredients in saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir at least half of hot mixture into egg yolks, then blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla. Pour immediately into baked pie shell.
Good served with Cool Whip.

title: ultimate sugar high
directions: Use 1 tablespoon butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place graham crackers as a bottom layer.
Spread frosting across crackers to desired thickness.
Melt marshmallows with 1/4 cup of butter in microwave for 1 minute.
Stir and cook on High 30 seconds more. Spread marshmallows over frosting.
Place graham crackers over marshmallows or crush crackers and sprinkle them over marshmallows.
Chill until ready to serve.
Cut in desired squares.

title: mud pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 8-inch round cake or pie pan.

title: stir-fry veggies
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add vegetables.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover; cook 10 minutes over medium heat.
Stir twice during cooking.

title: blueberry treat
directions: Use round or square casserole dish.
Spread soft cookie dough in and around dish.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg and lemon juice together, then spread over the cookie dough.
Add blueberry pie filling.
Bake, until cookie dough is done on the sides, at 350°. Let cool about 10 minutes, then chill.
Serve.

title: judy carter's chocolate cookies
directions: Stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Cream together butter, peanut butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Alternately blend dry ingredients and milk.
Dough will be soft.
Shape rounded teaspoons of mixture into balls.
Place at least 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until about done.
Remove from oven and gently press half marshmallow, cut side down.
Return to oven for 2 minutes. Let stand until frosting hardens.

title: broccoli-cauliflower rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except broccoli and cauliflower. Fold in vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use a large bowl or large rectangular baking dish.

title: turtles(candy)
directions: Melt margarine and caramels in double boiler.
When mixture is smooth, stir in nuts.
Drop by spoonful on buttered cookie sheet or wax paper.
Melt Hershey bars and paraffin, then dip cooled caramel and nuts in chocolate.
Place on buttered cookie sheet or wax paper to cool.
Use toothpick to dip candy.

title: peach cream salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice.
Add the jello and set aside to cool.
When cool, add buttermilk and the Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter or oleo in saucepan.
Add flour and cook, stirring, 3 minutes.
Add sour cream, onion, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
