title: molasses cake
directions: Mix and put in cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Then add flour, spices and tomato soup.
Bake in 350° oven, using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Make sure you grease pan.
Bake until done.

title: bread stuffing for poultry
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir onion and celery in butter until onion is tender.
Add to bread crumbs, cooked giblets and seasonings.
Add enough broth to moisten bread.

title: beef and barley soup
directions: In a 5 or 6-quart soup kettle or Dutch oven, combine beef, water and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling; skim off foam.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Remove beef and cut into bite-size pieces, discarding any bone and fat.
Return beef to pot.
Add carrots, onion, celery, barley, salt and pepper. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes, until barley is tender.
Stir in spinach (or Swiss chard) last 15 minutes of cooking time, if desired.

title: cheese ball with everything
directions: In a large bowl, beat together cream cheese and sour cream. Stir in Swiss cheese, Cheddar cheese, 1/3 bacon, onion, 1/2 pecans, relish, salt and pepper.
Shape into a ball.
In a small bowl, combine remaining bacon, pecans, parsley and poppy seed.
Roll cheese ball in this mixture.
Chill.

title: sock it to me
directions: Mix ingredients until creamy.
Pour half of the mixture in pan and spread cinnamon and brown sugar on top.
Pour rest of mixture on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
When cake is slightly warm, top with a powdered sugar glaze.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook the chicken breasts. Cut into bite size pieces. Heat together soup, sour cream, onion and chilies for about 5 minutes. Heat oil in skillet.
Soften tortillas in oil and drain on paper towels. Top each softened tortilla with chicken pieces and 2 tablespoons soup mixture. Roll up.
Arrange on greased baking dish. Pour remaining soup mixture over rolls.
Top with cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
May reheat in microwave oven.

title: ascension pie
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Mix in beaten eggs and melted butter.
Add Jack Daniels, chocolate chips and nuts.
Stir well.
Bake in unbaked pie crust in 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: easy beef burgers
directions: Place beef in roaster.
Add soup mix, bouillon cubes, garlic, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover container and roast in 250° oven for 5 hours.
Cool meat slightly and shred with fork; remove fat.
Put meat back in hot liquid.
Serve on buns.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate, stirring occasionally, for at least 8 hours or overnight.
Makes 3 quarts.
Great for picnics.

title: creamy corn spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir corns and butter in deep 2-quart baking dish.
Fold in sour cream and eggs; add corn muffin mix and blend well.
Bake until center of spoon bread is set approximately 1 hour.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake for an additional 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: mushroom burger patties
directions: Place patties in skillet (no grease).
Brown both sides. Remove patties.
Drain grease, pour mushrooms in skillet with juice and reduce liquid to half.
Pour in canned milk, cook until thick. Pour over patties.

title: fluffy icing
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar.
Boil sugar and water until soft ball stage.
Stop and remove from heat.
Add to egg whites and continue beating until slightly stiff.
Add marshmallows near end of beating time.

title: feather rolls
directions: Soak yeast in the lukewarm water.
Set aside 5 minutes.
In a medium size bowl, beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add to yeast mixture.
Mix sugar, margarine (room temperature) and salt like pie crust (crumbly).
Add 3 cups flour and egg mixture. Beat and then work in after cup of flour.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Fill large bowl 1/2 full of lettuce.
Add in order the layers of celery, onion, pepper and peas.
Spread salad dressing over peas and sprinkle on sugar.
Crumble bacon over top, then sprinkle cheese on.
Cover, refrigerate several hours.
Toss when about ready to serve.
Can put cheese on after tossed.

title: paul's chili
directions: In large Dutch oven, cook the ground beef and chopped onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in the undrained beans, tomatoes and green chili peppers.
Add the chili powder, garlic powder, oregano, ground red pepper and the pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, about 1 1/4 hours, or until desired consistency, stirring occasionally. Makes 12 (1-cup servings) with 226 calories, 17 g fat, 27 mg cholesterol and 10 g fiber.

title: viennese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat 2 eggs until frothy.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar gradually; add vanilla, melted chocolate and butter.
Combine baking powder and flour; add to chocolate mixture.
In a separate bowl, soften cream cheese; add 1 egg, sugar and almond flavor and mix.
In a greased baking pan, pour chocolate mix (half), then pour cream cheese mix on top of chocolate mix.
Spread remaining chocolate over cream cheese mix.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: jill's fish creole
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook the onion, green pepper and garlic in butter until tender, but not brown. Add undrained tomatoes, parsley flakes, bouillon granules and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Prepare instant pudding as directed on package.
Add whipped topping and mix until creamy.
Add sour cream and mix until creamy again.
Place layers of wafers and bananas in dish, placing the pudding mix between the layers, ending with mixture on top.
Let set.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: monkey bread(serves 8)
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters and shake in bag with sugar mixture.
Place in Bundt pan.
Do one can at a time.
Any sugar left, sprinkle over top.
Melt butter and mix with brown sugar. Bring to a boil.
Pour over top of layered biscuits.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes or until done.
I always add extra cinnamon after each shaking.

title: yogurt chocolate cake
directions: This cake is wonderful because it can be baked in a solar oven or on top of a stove using the "Dutch Oven Method."

title: "it" dessert
directions: Mix pineapple and cherries or strawberries together.
Add Eagle Brand condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Top with walnuts (optional).
Refrigerate several hours or freeze.
If frozen, take out 1/2 to 1 hour before serving.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Mix together well.
Serve on cocktail-rye bread or snack cracker.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix and chill overnight.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with 2/3 cup grated sharp Cheddar cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy chili casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add green pepper.
Cook until tender. Stir in corn, tomato sauce and chili powder.
Add 1/2 cup Cheez Whiz; stir until melted.
Spread 1 cup of meat mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with 1 cup chips.
Repeat layering twice.
Top with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining chips, tomatoes and Cheez Whiz.
Continue baking 5 more minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix well and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.
This recipe can be halved with good results.

title: baked grated carrots
directions: Place grated carrots in casserole.
Pour over them the melted margarine, lemon juice and sherry.
Sprinkle with chives.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mable apps soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, molasses and water. Add egg.

Sift together remaining ingredients. Combine all ingredients thoroughly and let stand about 10 minutes. Roll out on lightly floured board to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with round cookie cutter. Bake in moderately hot oven at 400° about 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: grub stew
directions: In pot, fill with water 3/4 of the way and add pork chops. Cook until done.
Remove pork chops and let cool.
Set aside.
In same pot you cook your pork chops and the same broth, add all your other ingredients.
Bring to boil and turn on low.
Cover and cook for about 45 to 60 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Take pork chops off the bone and chop or cut into nice size pieces.
Add to your pot of stew and any juice that drained off the pork chops; add to stew.
Let simmer for another 30 to 40 minutes.
Then add additional spices.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Slice meat into small bite size pieces. Brown in oil for 3 to 5 minutes. Set aside.
In a small pan, mix 2 cups of water with au jus mix and heat. Add to meat and put into a pressure cooker. Cook on simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until meat is tender.
Mix water, flour and brown gravy together.
Add to meat mixture.
Cook to thicken. Serve over hot noodles.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cook broccoli as directed on box. Place broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice together.
Spread over broccoli and chicken.
Cover the top with grated cheese and sprinkle croutons on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wassail bowl punch
directions: Combine all but orange and lemon slices.
Bring to a boil. Pour in bowl, then float the slices atop.
Yield:
4 quarts (16 cups or 20 punch cups).

title: broiled parmesan potatoes
directions: Stir together melted butter, basil, paprika, garlic powder and pepper.
Place potatoes in a single layer on broiler pan.
Brush mixture over both sides of potato.
Broil 5 inches from heat for 8 to 9 minutes.
Turn and sprinkle with cheese.
Broil a few more minutes.

title: round steak with gravy
directions: Coat round steak with flour.
Put in skillet with oil, brown (burn) both sides (the browner, the better).
Fill skillet with water until meat is covered.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Steak will be tender with gravy.

title: beef macaroni chili skillet(4 to 5 servings)
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in large frying pan; pour off drippings.
Add macaroni, salt, chili powder, sugar and pepper. Stir in 2 1/2 cups hot water, cover and cook 10 minutes.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar; cream well.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cover and freeze.
Take out of freezer approximately 1/2 hour before serving.
May top with walnuts or pecans.
Tastes like banana split; easy!

title: cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, salt and baking powder; add egg and milk and stir into cornmeal mixture until moist.
Put shortening into a 10-inch skillet and put into a preheated 425° oven.
As soon as shortening is hot, coat sides of skillet and stir remaining shortening into cornbread mixture.
Pour mixture into hot skillet and bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: honey-candied walnuts
directions: Bring to boil:
sugar, honey, salt and water and boil to 242° (or soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and walnuts. Stir until creamy.
(Will have "whitish" color.)
Turn onto waxed paper.
Separate nutmeats.

title: avocado salad
directions: Mix jello using 1/2 cup pineapple juice in place of equal amount of water.
When cool, add pineapple, lemon juice, salt and avocado.
Mix mayonnaise and whipped cream together; fold into jello mixture.
Place in greased molds.
Chill.
Unmold on lettuce leaves to serve.

title: chocolate sundae pie
directions: Combine milk, water, sugar, egg yolks, nutmeg and salt.
Cook over low heat until mixture starts to thicken (will not get very thick).

title: bean dip ole
directions: Cube Velveeta and stir over low heat.
Beat with all the ingredients until cheese melts.
Serve hot with corn or tortilla chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan the pretzels, brown sugar and 3/4 cup butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix the sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Pour over cooled pretzel crust.
Mix in a bowl the jello and hot water; stir and cool.
Add strawberries.
Allow to partially set in refrigerator.
Pour strawberry mixture over cooled cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate. Cut in squares.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Add melted butter, eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in unbaked, pastry shell.
Bake about 50 minutes in a slow oven at 325°.

title: best of bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal, oil and raisins in a large bowl.
Add boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Slightly combine eggs, buttermilk and molasses in a small bowl.
Add to cooled mixture.
Combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt; add to cereal mixture.
Stir just to moisten.
Cover batter with plastic wrap, wax paper or damp towel and let stand up to 1 hour.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400° in baking tins 3/4 full.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add with milk to saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Reduce heat and stir in chicken and pepper.
Return to boiling.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: steam cabbage(country style)
directions: Wash and shred cabbage.
Dice green pepper.
Cook bacon in medium size frypan, remove.
To hot pan add cabbage, green pepper, salt, pepper, sugar and water.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes. Serve topped with crumbled bacon strips.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Wash thoroughly and cook greens; drain well.
Make sure all water is out.
Make into patties, then dip in beaten eggs and then in fine bread crumbs.
Fry in oil.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook yellow rice mix according to directions, then mix all ingredients together, placing sliced cheese on top of mixture. Cook in the oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion and seasonings.
Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice by recipe on the box.
Add cheese soup, mushrooms and sliced chestnuts.
Mix.
Place in baking dish.
Put lightly salted chicken on top of rice mixture and dot with oleo.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Test for doneness, then serve.

title: judy's mashed potatoes
directions: Add cream cheese and butter to potatoes.
Add sour cream.
Add milk, eggs and salt.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Mix together to coat. Put on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Turn over after 20 minutes of baking. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: white fluffy frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick; cool completely.
Add margarine and Crisco; beat until mixed together.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until creamy.

title: california salad
directions: Layer first four ingredients in a bowl.
Cover with Miracle Whip, sprinkle with sugar and top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and chill.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread thinly on tortillas. Roll tortillas.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Slice in halves and dip in salsa.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts; spread nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Layer in an 8 x 10-inch pan: 1/3 sauce, 1/2 uncooked lasagna pieces, 1 cup cottage cheese and 1/2 of Mozzarella. Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
May be refrigerated or frozen at this point.
To cook, cover casserole and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
If casserole is frozen, thaw before baking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: devil dog cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Let cool, then fill with filling and add top cookie.

title: apricot pound cake
directions: Bake at 350° in tube pan until done.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Place chicken breasts in greased shallow glass baking dish. Combine onion soup mix with the mushroom soup and spread on the chicken breasts.
Cover securely with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: bill's nachos
directions: Spread the chips in a single layer on a paper plate.
Sprinkle with a thin layer of the Cheddar cheese.
Cook in microwave on High power for 30 to 45 seconds or until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.
One plate per person.
This makes a great after school treat.
You can use crackers if you do not have tortilla chips.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Blend together all ingredients with mixer. Pour into bundt pan. Bake at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix together, then beat at medium speed for a few minutes. Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° until done.
Frost with 7-Up Cake Icing.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: In a large saucepan, heat butter and oil.
Add mushrooms and saute 5 minutes.
Remove mushrooms and reserve.
Add flour to pan juice and stir to form soup.
Cook until bubbly.
Slowly add broth and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add cream, sherry, Parmesan cheese and nutmeg; stir until cheese melts.
Add turkey and reserved mushrooms.
Stir well.
Combine with spaghetti and turn into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 3-quart casserole. Melt 2 tablespoons butter and toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine and heat soups and seasonings.
Mix well.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with chips, chicken, 1/2 of sauce and cheese.
Repeat.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken curry
directions: Cook the chicken (boil it !). Cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Saute the celery and onion in a little margarine until tender crisp; set aside.
Simmer the soups and curry powder for at least one hour.
Add celery, onion, mushrooms and chicken and heat through.
Serve over rice with condiments on the side.
Peanuts, raisins, currants, green onion, bacon bits, coconut, green pepper, boiled eggs, etc.
Serves 12 - 16.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 450°.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat peanut butter, butter, vanilla and salt until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then confectioners sugar until smooth.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on baking sheet.
Chill until firm.
With toothpick, dip each into melted candy coating.
Place on wax paper.
Let stand or chill until firm.

title: hawaiian wedding cake with frosting
directions: Mix flour, soda, sugar, salt, eggs, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate poodles
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat, add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Mix in rolled oats and stir until all are covered.
Add vanilla.
Spoon onto cookie sheet or waxed paper and let cool until hard.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
I always double this recipe.
Delicious served with milk while warm.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix everything together.
Place on stove and bring to a rolling boil, stirring often.
Turn on simmer and cook 1 to 2 hours.

title: garden bean salad
directions: Drain all cans of beans and place in a large bowl.
Add green pepper, celery, pimentos and green onions.
Set aside.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil in a heavy saucepan and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and immediately pour over vegetables. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: corn dogs
directions: You will also need wooden skewers.

title: cabbage with pepper sauce
directions: Cut cabbage into 12 wedges. Heat water and salt to boiling in 10-inch skillet; add cabbage wedges. Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer until cabbage is crisp-tender, 10 to 15 minutes; drain.

title: hawaiian beans
directions: Mix salad and beans.
Mix brown sugar and cornstarch.
Mix with beans. Put pineapple on top.
Can also put part of pineapple in mixture and the rest on top.

title: rosemary pineapple cooler
directions: Simmer 1 cup pineapple juice for 5 minutes with herbs; strain. Add water, sugar, lemon juice, limeade and rest of pineapple juice.
Chill.
Serves 25.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Now add alternately with milk to other mixture.
Beat all together.
Put in paper baking cups and bake in a moderate oven 30 minutes.
Frost with chocolate icing.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar. Mix with remaining ingredients. Mix well and freeze. Makes 25 cupcake size or a 9 x 13 dish.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into hot dog or hamburger rolls.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: french onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Add bouillon and sherry.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole.

title: mexican zucchini
directions: In large skillet, heat olive oil on high, saute all vegetables at once for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add basil, picante, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Cover and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Add cheese and mix well.

title: barbecued venison
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.
Pour over 3 pounds of venison which has been sauteed in hot fat to brown.
Roast in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 to 2 hours, turning occasionally.

title: mexican tostito chip dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Cut cheese into small squares. Combine all ingredients in crock-pot on high.
(For faster results, mixture can be microwaved.)
Serve as a hearty dip with Tostitos-style chips.

title: mississippi punch
directions: Puree strawberries and peaches and mix in sugar.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Spoon into punch bowl and pour champagne over.
(Place ice ring in bowl if desired.) Float strawberries on top.

title: taco peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place pepper halves in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain well.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Meanwhile, brown turkey in skillet; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, kidney beans and salsa.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
Spoon into pepper halves.
Cover; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with one teaspoon of sour cream, 1 teaspoon tomato and 1 teaspoon of Cheddar cheese.

title: martha's version of mammaw oakes'           pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased and floured bundt or tube pan. (Pan may be sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.) Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: reverse chocolate cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, cocoa, milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.

title: noodle rice pilaf
directions: In saucepan, over medium-high heat, saute vermicelli until browned, stirring constantly.
Stir in rice.
Stir in broth. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and broth is absorbed.
Serves 6.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix juice, margarine and sugar in mixer; refrigerate 1 hour. Add nuts and wafers.
Roll into balls the size of a small walnut and then roll in coconut.
Makes 16 dozen.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli,
bacon
and raisins.
Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Mix all together; chill and serve.

title: southern bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in a shallow 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream or a lemon sauce.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Really good.
Top with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: no sugar pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done and knife comes out clean.

title: elegantly scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins.
Cool, peel and cut into cubes.
In saucepan over low heat, combine butter and cheese.
Stir until almost melted.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Fold into potatoes; put into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes with glass or foil cover.
Stir before serving hot.

title: crescent-wrapped gouda(8 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut cheese round in half to form 2 circles.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Press each into a 6 x 6-inch rectangle.

title: grandpa's original sausage or summer salami
directions: Mix
all
ingredients thoroughly.
Keep meat chilled at all times.
For sausage, stuff in hog casings approximately 3 cups. Let
sit
in
refrigerator	or
cold place overnight to blend flavors.
Poach
in
water	and
serve.
Fresh
sausage should
be frozen for storage or smoked.
For salami, stuff in beef middles (approximately 2 packages).
Let sit in refrigerator
or
cold place overnight to blend flavors.
Smoke at 95° for
days or until sweating stops.
Hang in cold, dry place to
harden.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: Cream margarine and add rest of ingredients.
Turn into a well-greased pie plate.
Pat down with moistened fingers to the edge.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until a golden brown.

title: basinger's bakery fresh cinnamon buns
directions: In a large bowl, combine the mashed potatoes and potato water. Add shortening.
Blend well.
Add the salt, sugar and egg.
In a small bowl, combine the yeast and lukewarm water, stirring until dissolved.
Add the yeast mixture to the potato mixture.
Add the milk alternately with the flour.
Knead the dough and place in a large bowl.
Grease the top of the dough with the butter or margarine.
Place in the refrigerator overnight.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix all fruit together with dry pudding; chill. Serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix fruit. Add boxes of jello. Mix well. Chill and serve.

title: triple-onion baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: easy lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan. Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes. Pour into pan.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Stir eggs, onions, corn and cottage cheese.
Add Cheez Whiz, oleo and broccoli.
Mix well; add Jiffy mix.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and flavoring.
Add sugar and then eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Start cake in cold oven.
Cook at 300° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add pineapple.
Stir in bread cubes.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking pan, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes until lightly browned.
Good hot or cold.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, butter and vanilla
bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add flour and baking soda; mix well. Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: steven's favorite pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Make a well in the center and add other ingredients; mix well.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes in 2 greased loaf pans.
This freezes very well.

title: pearl's corn pudding no. 3
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, together.
Put half of the mixture in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Add remaining mixture and top with cheese.
Bake in a moderate oven until done.

title: butterscotch bar cookies
directions: Mix all together except the sugar, bits and nuts.
Put in greased oblong pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar, then 1/2 bag of butterscotch bits and 1 cup chopped walnuts or pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas milk punch
directions: Mix honey, cinnamon, salt, vanilla, ginger, nutmeg and milk together in punch bowl.
Spoon scoops of vanilla ice cream over punch.
Sprinkle with crushed peppermint candy.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Add milk, broccoli, soup and cheese; cook over low heat until broccoli is thawed and cheese is melted. Add rice; pour into casserole and bake until bubbly and brown on top.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine margarine, peanut butter, sugar and cracker crumbs and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and pour on top. Chill and cut into small pieces.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Heat pineapple and strawberries to a boil.
Add dash of salt. Stir in jello and cool to room temperature.
Stir in buttermilk and chill until partially set.
Stir in package Cool Whip.

title: collector's cocoa cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until very fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients 5 times.
Combine dry ingredients alternately with water and the creamed mixture. Bake in loaf or layer pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for loaf or less for layers.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, then remove.

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Wash and cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces. Chop celery and mushrooms.
Grate onion.
Mix all together.
Mix all other ingredients together in a bowl; pour over vegetables. Toss and refrigerate for at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: green bean casserole(this is so basic and yet everybody loves it)
directions: Drain beans well and mix with onion and soup.
Put in casserole dish and top with the French fried onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown and season hamburger, then add package onion soup and brown more.
Remove from heat and drain grease of hamburger (brown hamburger in own juice).
Put in pan.
Mix can tomato soup with hamburger.
Drain corn and green beans.
Mix in hamburger and tomato soup.
Boil potatoes and whip them as you would for mashed potatoes.
Put on top of hamburger and vegetables.
Apply cheese slices over top and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cheese will turn a little brown.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Warm the applesauce.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg and mix well.
Add applesauce.
Sift flour, spices and soda together.
Add slowly to applesauce mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts and raisins. Bake in 325° oven.

title: cavitini
directions: Cook rigatoni by package directions.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and mushrooms and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 layer shredded cheese.
Place sliced pepperoni evenly over cheese, then cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: basic muffins
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in bowl.
In separate bowl, mix next 3 ingredients.
Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients.
Mix gently; do not overmix.
Put in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
(May add raisins, nuts or blueberries.)

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove wrappers from kisses.
In large bowl, beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add flour; blend until smooth.
Stir in small chocolate chips.
Mold scant tablespoon of dough around each piece of kiss, covering completely.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set; do not undercook.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash.
Drain well.
Combine sour cream, cheese, butter, salt and paprika.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and onion.
Blend well and combine squash.
Pour into casserole and cover with crumbled cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake at 375° until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix milk, peanut butter, egg, and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix, mix well and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into balls and cook in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Drain excess oil.

title: margie's congealed lime dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve Jell-O in hot water and set aside to cool.
Thoroughly mix mayonnaise, cottage cheese and sweetened condensed milk.
Add pineapple and pecans; blend with Jell-O.
Chill in refrigerator until congealed.

title: white chocolate salties
directions: Combine chocolate and shortening in top of a double boiler. Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until chocolate melts.
Pour chocolate mixture into a large mixing bowl.
Stir in pretzels and peanuts.
Spread into a buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Chill 20 minutes or until firm.
Break into pieces.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: veggie appetizers
directions: Bake crescent rolls on cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°; let cool.
Or use white sandwich bread with the crusts removed.
Mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix until very soft and creamy.
Spread mixture over rolls.
Chop vegetables very finely and mix with the Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheeses; sprinkle on bread.
Pat lightly and chill until used.
Cut in small squares or triangles.
Decorate with sliced black olives, pecans, dill weed, parsley, etc.

title: mom's salad dressing
directions: Mix all together and then add soup.
Stir well.
Makes 2 1/2 small (8 ounce) bottles.
Keep in refrigerator.
Can be given as gifts at Christmas.
I use leftover glass bottles from Kraft dressing.
Just tie a red bow around the neck of each bottle.

title: lemon sour cream pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan; add butter, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Cool.
Fold in sour cream. Spoon into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: guacamole with tortilla chips(makes 12 appetizer servings)
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water; pour into blender container.

Add cottage cheese, avocado, 1/2 cup green onions, jalapeno peppers, lemon juice, garlic and chili powder; cover. Blend on low speed, scraping down sides occasionally, about 2 minutes or until mixture is smooth.
Pour into shallow 5-cup serving dish; smooth top.
Chill until set, about 4 hours.

title: meltaway mints
directions: Beat butter and shortening together.
Add sugar alternately with water.
Beat in extract and food coloring.
Knead.
Roll on wax paper. Cut in thin slices.
Let dry on wax paper.
Let stand 24 hours until dry.
Pack and store.
Keep in covered container.

title: jello pie
directions: Dissolve jello with hot water.
Add frozen strawberries, then add Cool Whip.
Put it into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: grandma's scalloped potatoes(for a large group)
directions: Layer potatoes, soups and cheese in Nesco roaster.
Cover with enough milk so you can see it come to the top of the potatoes.
Start at 400° and turn down to 300° when it starts to bubble.
Cook for about another 3 to 4 hours or until potatoes are fork-tender.

title: chicken dijon with artichokes
directions: In a large nonstick skillet that has been sprayed with Pam, saute chicken in liquid Butter Buds. Remove from pan and cube. Add flour to pan; stir until smooth. You might need to add 2 or 3 more tablespoons liquid Butter Buds if it is too dry. Stir in broth and skim milk. Add mustard.
Add artichoke hearts and chicken; simmer in sauce for 30 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles. I prefer using bow tie noodles. Serves 8. Contains 1.4 g fat and 259 calories.

title: roast beef
directions: Put seasonings on meat.
Pour wine over roast.
Roast meat, uncovered, in oven at 325° to desired degree of doneness.
Turn part way through.
Make gravy with drippings.
Serve with mashed potatoes.
One of Kristen's favorites.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, cornstarch, cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk and egg yolks (slightly beaten).
Boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: pineapple rice
directions: Cook rice until tender; drain.
Add sugar and pineapple; let cool, then add Cool Whip.
Stir until well blended.
